  •      (13 July – 26 September 2024)

  •      (27 September 2024 – 16 October 2024)
  • Killing of Yahya Sinwar
  •      (17 October 2024 – present)

October 2024

17 October

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 29 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 42,438.[1][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that at least 45 people were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours.[2]
  • SANA reported that the IDF struck Latakia.[3] It also reported that "anti-aircraft defence intercepted hostile targets" and fire erupted after the attack. The Syrian Observatory for Human Rights reported that it "targeted a weapons depot".[4]
  • Rockets and a drone were launched towards Israel.[5]
  • The US struck five underground weapons facilities in Houthi-controlled territory in Yemen using B-2 bombers.[6] The Houthis vowed to respond after the strikes.[7]
  • Hezbollah said that it fired a barrage of rockets towards Safed and targeted an IDF base to the east of Netanya with Nasr-1 guided surface-to-surface missile. It also released a video of an Israeli tank engulfed by fire after the attack.[8]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it launched a drone towards Eilat.[9]
  • Quds News Network reported that Israeli forces assaulted the family of two men arrested by them in al-Fawar camp, south of Hebron.[10]
  • Israeli soldiers raised the Israeli flag in the vicinity of a monument in Labbouneh, southern Lebanon.[11]
  • At least 100 Hezbollah targets were struck one day prior.[12]
  • Approximately 30 rockets were launched towards Upper Galilee. Hezbollah said that it targeted a gathering of Israeli soldiers in al-Sadana, Shebaa Farms.[13]
  • Many families were trapped after their houses were bombed in a neighborhood at the entry point of the northern cities in the Gaza Strip.[14]
  • The IDF struck Tamnine Al Tahta in the Bekaa Valley and ordered residents of nearby Saraain al-Tahta to evacuate from their houses.[15]
  • A German warship operating under UNIFIL intercepted a drone off the coast of Lebanon.[16][17]
  • Hezbollah claimed that it struck two Merkava tanks with guided missiles near Labbouneh.[18]
  • The International Labour Organization said that almost 100 percent of Gaza's population is facing poverty.[19]
  • Israeli forces shot and killed a 60-year-old Palestinian woman who was picking olives in Faqqua. Israeli forces also fired on an event organised by the Colonization and Wall Resistance Commission for helping farmers from Kafr al-Labad pick olives from their lands.[20]
  • Israeli strikes on an UNRWA-run school serving as a shelter for displaced people in Jabalia killed at least 28 people, including women and children and injured 160 others. The IDF said that it carried out a "precise strike on an operational meeting" of 18 Hamas and PIJ militants who were involved in rocket attacks targeting Israeli territory and planning and committing attacks targeting Israeli soldiers and Israel in recent days without offering evidence. Hamas denied the claim.[21][22][23]
  • The polio vaccination campaign for children from two to ten years old was completed in central Gaza. Vaccination for children in Khan Yunis and Rafah governorates will start on 19 October and will continue for four days, followed by children in northern Gaza.[24]
  • Israel said that they killed three gunmen in Tal as-Sultan.[25][26] Dental records identified one of the deceased as Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar, who was also found to be carrying large amounts of shekels and personal identification documents.[27] Hamas also confirmed his death.[28]
  • An Israeli air strike on a residential building in the Maghazi refugee camp killed at least 10 people, including women and children.[29][30]
  • Five Israeli soldiers were killed and an IDF officer and two soldiers were critically wounded while fighting in south Lebanon, increasing the IDF death toll in the invasion on Lebanon to 21. Nine other Israeli soldiers were also critically wounded while fighting in south Lebanon and the Gaza Strip.[31][32]
  • Hezbollah claimed that it destroyed two Israeli surveillance drones. It also announced that it is moving to a new escalatory stage in the confrontation and said that it will become clear in the coming days.[33]
  • Hezbollah said that it targeted Israeli soldiers on the outskirts of Kafr Kila using artillery. It also said that its forces hit a gathering of Israeli soldiers on two occasions near Aita al-Shaab.[34]
  • Israeli soldiers detonated several explosives in Muhajbib, demolishing most of the historic village. The IDF said that it destroyed a Redwan tunnel network in the center of the village.[35]

18 October

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 62 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 42,500.[36][a]
  • Palestinian armed groups targeted Israeli forces using explosive devices and guns in Tubas.[37]
  • The World Health Organization alleged that Israel was blocking medical specialists from entering Gaza.[38]
  • The IDF claimed to have killed Hezbollah commander Mohammad Hussein Ramal in an air strike in Taybeh. It also said that it located and destroyed rocket launchers aimed for attacking northern Israel and discovered Hezbollah weapons in southern Lebanon. The IAF also struck a militant cell it said was preparing to launch an antitank missile towards Israeli soldiers operating in southern Lebanon.[39]
  • The IDF said that its air force conducted approximately 150 strikes on sites in the Gaza and Lebanon one day prior including munitions warehouses, rocket launch sites, and sniper and observation posts, and killed dozens of militants.[40]
  • An Israeli air strike on a school serving as a shelter for displaced people in the centre of the Jabalia refugee camp injured several people, mostly children.[41]
  • An Israeli missile strike on a house in Nassr Street northwest of Gaza City killed several children.[42]
  • A 12-year-old boy died from the injuries sustained in an Israeli strike in Al-Aqsa Martyrs Hospital four days prior.[42][43]
  • The IDF said that it identified militants crossing from Jordan towards the south of the Dead Sea region and killed two of them after they fired on Israeli forces. Two Israeli soldiers were injured in the attack,[44][45] which was claimed by the Muslim Brotherhood in Jordan.[46]
  • Three people were killed after Israeli forces attacked Jabalia.[47]
  • Israeli soldiers detained a young shepherd while Israeli settlers stole his herd of sheep in Jurish.[48]
  • Israeli forces cut off communication and internet networks in northern Gaza, particularly in Jabalia.[49]
  • A home in al-Faluja area of Jabalia was demolished by Israeli bulldozers with a displaced family inside it.[50]
  • Seventy-five projectiles were launched by Hezbollah from Lebanon towards Israel,[51] including 20 rockets. Some of them targeted the Philon IDF Base in Rosh Pinna,[52] an air missile defence base east of Hadera,[53] a gathering of soldiers in Safed,[54] and an area north of Haifa.[51]
  • The IDF announced that it killed 60 Hezbollah fighters during combat in southern Lebanon the day prior.[55]
  • The Belgian Prosecutor's Office said that a Belgian-Israeli soldier was under investigation for possible war crimes in Gaza.[56]
  • An Israeli air strike on several houses in the vicinity of the Nassar Junction in Jabalia refugee camp killed 33 people including women and children and injured 85 others.[57][58][59]
  • An Israeli strike on a home in the Maghazi refugee camp killed 16 people, left several people missing and trapped under the rubble.[60][61]
  • Three rockets targeting the Haifa Bay were intercepted by the IDF.[62]
  • An Israeli reservist of the Alon Brigade [he]'s 5030th Battalion who was critically injured during combat in southern Lebanon on 9 October died from his wounds, bringing the IDF death toll since the start of invasion of Lebanon to 22.[63]

19 October

  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that at least 36 people were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 48 hours.[64]
  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 19 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 42,519.[65][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that at least 16 people were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours.[66]
  • A drone launched from Syria crashed in the northern Golan Heights.[67]
  • Palestinian armed groups targeted Israeli forces using guns and explosive devices in Balata refugee camp.[68]
  • The US Central Command destroyed 20 "Iranian-supplied" one-way attack drones and land attack cruise missiles in various parts of the Middle East in one week. It also said that Iran-backed militias in Iraq targeted US and coalition forces with rocket attacks two times.[69]
  • Three drones were launched from Lebanon towards Israel, one of which hit Benjamin Netanyahu's residence in Caesarea.[70] Hezbollah claimed responsibility for the attack.[71]
    • Hezbollah said that it also launched suicide drones towards Shlomi, an IDF base in Nesher, Kiryat Shmona and a group of Israeli soldiers in al-Marj and Zarit.[72]
  • An Israeli drone shot dead a Palestinian child, while Israeli forces attacked those trying to rescue the child in al-Nafaq Street in central Gaza.[73]
  • Clashes were reported between Israeli soldiers and Hamas operatives in Jabalia refugee camp in the past 24 hours.[74]
  • Two people were killed after Israeli forces bombed Jounieh, north of Beirut.[75]
  • One person was killed and several others were injured after Israeli forces attacked the entrance of the laboratory of Kamal Adwan Hospital in Beit Lahia.[76]
  • One hundred rockets were launched from Lebanon towards northern Israel, damaging a residential building in Shlomi.[77][78][79] Hezbollah said that it launched rockets towards a region north of Haifa. A person died and at least 13 people were injured in the rocket strikes.[80][81]
  • The IDF said that it killed Nasser Abd al-Aziz Rashid, deputy commander of Hezbollah's operations in Bint Jbeil District. It added that its forces located and destroyed stockpiles of weapons in southern Lebanon, "eliminated" two militant squads in Rafah, and destroyed Hamas military facilities in central Gaza and targeted militants in Jabalia.[78]
  • Two patients in the ICU of the Indonesia Hospital died after Israeli forces destroyed its generator.[82]
  • An Israeli strike on UNRWA-affiliated Asmaa School serving as shelter for displaced people in Al-Shati refugee camp killed nine people and injured several people including children.[83][84][85]
  • A Palestinian was shot and injured by Israeli forces in Qalandia Camp, northeast of Jerusalem.[86]
  • Over 450 people were killed since the start of Second battle of Jabalia.[87]
  • The IDF carried out a mass arrest campaign in evacuation centres in northern Gaza and took those arrested to undisclosed locations.[88]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents in Haret Hreik[89] and Bourj el-Barajneh.[90]
  • An Israeli air strike on a residential apartment in Baaloul killed four people including the mayor of Sohmor, Haidar Shahla, and injured several others.[91]
  • An Israeli strike on al-Balad area of Jabalia refugee camp killed five people, most of them children and injured several others.
  • The IDF said that it targeted Hezbollah's intelligence command centre and several munitions warehouses in several locations in the southern suburbs of Beirut.[92]
  • Two Israeli soldiers were killed while fighting in northern Gaza, bringing the IDF death toll in Gaza to 357. An explosive laden-drone critically injured an IDF officer in southern Lebanon.[93]
  • An Israeli reserve soldier died of injuries he had sustained in an October 9 clash with Hezbollah fighters in Lebanon, increasing the number of Israeli soldiers killed as a result of that clash to two.[94]
  • An Israeli strike on a clearly marked vehicle despite prior coordination with Israeli authorities killed four water engineers and workers of Coastal Municipalities Water Utility, a partner of Oxfam while they were on their way for repairing water infrastructure in Khuza'a, east of Khan Yunis.[95][96]
  • A young Palestinian man was killed when an four-wheel drive of IDF run over him in Anabta.[97]
  • Approximately 200 projectiles were launched by Hezbollah towards Israel.[98]
  • A Hezbollah member captured in southern Lebanon died in the custody of Israeli soldiers.[99]
  • At least 87 people including women and children were killed or missing and 40 others were injured in an Israeli airstrike on several homes and a multistory residential building in Beit Lahia. The IDF said that it precisely struck Hamas militants.[100][101][102]
  • Five people were injured after Israeli forces bombed a building adjacent to a group of tents made for displaced Palestinians in Deir al-Balah.[103]
  • An Israeli missile strike killed an Iranian woman and her Lebanese husband in Beirut. They survived an initial strike.[104]

20 October

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 84 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 42,603.[105][a]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents to move at least 500 metres away from at least two buildings in Haret Hreik and Hadath.[106] It also issued evacuation orders for some areas in the east of Lebanon for the first time in a week.[107]
  • The IDF said that its air force struck 175 militant targets in Gaza and Lebanon, striking weapons warehouses, rocket launch sites and other Hamas and Hezbollah infrastructure. It also said that it intercepted a "suspicious aerial target" off the coast of Haifa.[108]
  • The IDF claimed to have killed key Hezbollah officials Elhag Abbas Salameh, Racha Abbas Icha, and Ahmed Ali Hasin in its strike on Hezbollah intelligence headquarters in southern Beirut. It also said that it hit an underground weapons workshop in Beirut.[109] It also claimed to have killed Alhaj Abbas Salameh, a senior figure in the Hezbollah's southern command, Radja Abbas Awache, a Hezbollah communications expert and Ahmad Ali Hussein, who was responsible for development of Hezbollah's strategic weapons, in airstrikes.[110]
  • At least 160 rockets were launched from Lebanon to Israel. Rockets were launched to places in northern Israel including areas in Safed, Haifa, Acre and Margaliot.[111] Hezbollah said that it targeted an IDF base in the vicinity of Safed[112] and Shebaa Farms.[113]
  • Israeli forces bombed a vehicle belonging to the Lebanese Armed forces on a road between Ain Ebel and Hanine in Bint Jbeil District, killing three soldiers.[114] The IDF subsequently apologised, saying that they had been mistaken for militants.[115]
  • The al-Qassam Brigades claimed to have killed and injured Israeli soldiers by targeting two personnel carriers using a Shawaz explosive device and a Yassin-105 rocket launcher in the east and west of the Jabalia refugee camp.[116]
  • The Palestinian Central Bureau of Statistics said that five of its employees were killed since October 2023.[117]
  • The IDF said that it killed dozens of militants in close-quarter encounters on the ground and airstrikes across Gaza.[118]
  • Hezbollah said that it launched rockets towards Israeli soldiers in the outskirts of Markaba and west of Odaisseh.[119]
  • An Israeli strike on a small grocery shop in Deir al-Balah killed four people including an elderly woman.[120]
  • Armed Israeli settlers attacked Palestinian olive farmers in Ramin Valley, east of Tulkarm, and in Burqa, and stole olive harvests in Masafer Yatta.[121]
  • The IDF destroyed several villages in southern Lebanon including Ramyah, razing its homes and mosques.[122]
  • Ehsan Daxa, the commander of the IDF's 401st Armoured Brigade, who was of Druze ethnicity and held a rank of colonel in the IDF, was killed by explosive devices in Jabalia after exiting his tank. Another IDF officer was critically wounded in Gaza.[123][124]
  • The IDF demolished a UNIFIL observation tower and perimeter fence in Marwahin.[125]
  • Several Israeli airstrikes targeted branches of the Hezbollah-linked Al-Qard Al-Hasan Association bank in Beirut and the Beqaa Valley. One strike hit in close proximity to Beirut–Rafic Hariri International Airport.[126]
  • Hezbollah claimed that its air defense unit shot down an Israeli Hermes 450 drone.[127]
  • Several people were injured after Israeli forces bombed a house in the al-Tawbah Mosque area of Jabalia camp.[128]

21 October

  • About 170 projectiles were launched by Hezbollah from Lebanon to Israel.[129]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it launched a drone towards an IDF target in the Golan Heights.[130]
  • COGAT said that 114 aid trucks entered Gaza a day prior.[131]
  • Clashes were reported between Israeli soldiers and Palestinian fighters in Rafah.[132]
  • The IDF arrested 18 people including two children in the West Bank.[133]
  • Hezbollah fired rockets towards an Israeli artillery position in Odem, Kiryat Shmona, targeted Israeli forces in al-Malkiyeh IDF site, an IDF base in Beit Lahia and targeted Israeli forces in Khalet Warda and Mizra. It also said that it targeted Israel soldiers operating in Maroun al-Ras.[134]
  • The IDF said that it hit approximately 15 short-range Hezbollah rocket launchers in southern Lebanon. It also said some of those launchers were used for recent attacks in northern Israel and added that it hit buildings used by Hezbollah in various areas of southern Lebanon.[135]
  • Israeli forces and settlers attacked Palestinian olive farmers and international activists supporting them using toxic gas in Beit Lid.[136]
  • Israeli artillery struck a crowd fleeing UN-run schools serving as shelter for displaced people in Jabalia refugee camp after an Israeli evacuation order, killing at least seven people.[137]
  • An Israeli strike on a tent in the al-Mawasi humanitarian zone killed at least two people, including a child, and injured six others.[138]
  • Shrapnel from a Hezbollah rocket attack lightly injured a man in Ayelet HaShahar.[139]
  • Israeli police arrested seven Israelis suspected of spying for Iran.[140]
  • The al-Qassam Brigades claimed that its fighters killed and injured Israeli soldiers by ambushing four IDF vehicles loaded with explosives in the Jabalia refugee camp.[141]
  • Syrian state media reported that a guided missile attack on a car in Mezzeh killed at least two people and injured three others.[142][143] The IDF said that it killed the commander of a Hezbollah unit responsible for the transfer of weapons from Iran.[144]
  • An Israeli air strike on a building in Baalbek killed six people including a child.[145][146]
  • Israeli forces killed six men trying to get drinking water in Jabalia refugee camp.[147]
  • An Israeli strike on an area sheltering displaced people in Jabalia killed four Palestinians, including two women.[147]
  • Israeli artillery shelling on a school sheltering displaced people in Jabalia killed at least 10 people including children and injured several others.[148]
  • Hezbollah launched a "large missile barrage" towards Yoav IDF camp in the Golan Heights. Israeli Home Command said that sirens sounded in Margaliot and Manara.[149]
  • Several Palestinian children and young men were briefly detained and assaulted by Israeli soldiers during IDF raid in Az-Zawiya. A Palestinian child was beaten before being detained in Kafr Qallil.[150]
  • The Israeli Broadcasting Authority reported a suspected hack at the port database of Haifa.[151]
  • Hezbollah said that it targeted an IDF intelligence base in the suburbs of Tel Aviv.[152]
  • An Israeli airstrike in Kharayeb killed four people.[153]
  • Israeli airstrikes killed four paramedics in Babliyeh and one each in Khirbet Selm, Bir el-Sanasel and Deir Ez Zahrani.[153]
  • An Israeli airstrike near the Rafik Hariri University Hospital in Beirut killed at least 18 people, including four children, and injured at least 60 others.[154][155][156]

22 October

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 115 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 48 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 42,718.[157][a]
  • The Lebanese government reported that at least 63 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon in the past 24 hours.[158]
  • A barrage of rockets was launched towards Beit Aryeh-Ofarim.[159] Hezbollah claimed to have hit the Nirit area in suburbs of Tel Aviv. A state of emergency was declared in Tel Aviv.[160][161]
  • Israel said it struck over 230 militant targets in Gaza and Lebanon in the past 24 hours.[162]
  • Hezbollah claimed to have hit the Glilot base of Unit 8200 in the suburbs of Tel Aviv using missiles.[163]
  • Hezbollah also launched medium-range rockets to Haifa.[164] It claimed to have hit Stella Maris naval base, northwest of Haifa. Hezbollah also launched missiles towards an area north of Caesarea.[165]
  • An Israeli drone strike on a group of Palestinians in Beit Lahia killed at least 15 people including women and children and injured several others.[166]
  • Falling interceptor fragments injured a man in Ma'agan Michael and damaged a residential building and several cars in the same area.[167]
  • Sixteen Israeli soldiers were injured while fighting in Lebanon.[168]
  • Israeli drones equipped with loudspeakers ordered families in Beit Lahia to flee through some roads leading to military checkpoints. Later, Palestinian men were arrested and were taken to undisclosed locations. Women were transferred to Gaza City.[169]
  • The IDF arrested 28 Palestinians including a child in the West Bank.[170]
  • The IDF said that it struck a Hezbollah naval base in Beirut used to store fast boats, carry out tests and train naval forces. It added that its other attacks hit weapons depots, command centres and other infrastructure. It also said that some of them were underground targets.[171]
  • The al-Qassam Brigades claimed to have killed and injured 12 Israeli soldiers by detonating an antipersonnel explosive device in the al-Faluja area of the Jabalia refugee camp.[172]
  • The al-Qassam Brigades said that it struck two Israeli D9 bulldozers using a Yassin 105 rocket and a Shawaz explosive device in the al-Faluja area of Jabalia. It added that its fighters attacked another Israeli D9 bulldozer in al-Saftawi Street north of Gaza City using a ground bomb.[173]
  • Hezbollah said that its rocket strike targeted Israeli soldiers gathered in the west of Odaisseh. It also said that it targeted Hatzor using rockets.[174]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents to move at least 500 metres away from two buildings in Ghobeiry.[175]
  • The Houthis said that it targeted an IDF base in Tel Aviv with "hypersonic" ballistic missiles.[176]
  • The Al-Quds Brigades claimed that it killed Israeli soldiers by targeting IDF vehicles with explosives in the west of the Jabalia refugee camp.[177]
  • An Israeli strike in Nabatieh injured three paramedics.[178]
  • Hezbollah confirmed that some of its fighters were captured by the IDF.[179]
  • The FBI announced an investigation into an alleged leak of US intelligence documents on Israeli plans to attack Iran.[180]
  • Seven Jerusalem residents were arrested by Israeli authorities over an alleged Iranian intelligence plot to assassinate an Israeli scientist and mayor.[181]
  • The IAF said that it struck ten Hezbollah command and control centers in Al Housh, southern Lebanon within the past 24 hours.[182]
  • An 11-year-old Palestinian child died after being shot by Israeli forces in Nablus for throwing a stone at an armoured IDF jeep in the distance.[183]
  • An Israeli artillery shelling in al-Balad area of Jabalia killed five people including children and injured 27 others.[184]
  • Hezbollah fired ten rockets at Neot Mordechai, killing an Israeli reservist from the 7338th "Adirim" Artillery Brigade's 508th battalion and seriously injuring three other reservists.[185][186][187]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it targeted an IDF target in the Golan Heights with a drone strike.[188]
  • Approximately 140 projectiles were launched from Lebanon by Hezbollah towards Israel. Hezbollah said that it launched kamikaze drones towards Eliakim IDF base south of Haifa.[189]
  • A reservist major who served as the deputy commander of the IDF's Alon Brigade [he]'s 9308th battalion was killed during combat in southern Lebanon.[187]
  • A third Israeli soldier was killed on the same day; the IDF stated the soldier was killed in a military-related car crash near the Gaza border.[190]
  • The IDF confirmed the killing of Hashem Safieddine and 23 other members of Hezbollah's intelligence unit in an airstrike in Dahieh on 3 October after their bodies were reportedly found in the bunker that was struck.[191][192] Hezbollah also confirmed his death.[193]
  • An Israeli airstrike on a house in Teffahta killed 19 people.[194]
  • A woman trapped under rubble in Gaza City for five days was rescued by the Palestinian Civil Defence.[195]
  • Hezbollah drone attack on Israel sends a million people to shelters.[196]

23 October

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 74 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 42,792.[197][a]
  • The Lebanese government reported that at least 28 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon in the past 24 hours.[198]
  • An Israeli strike on a house in the az-Zarqa area of Gaza City killed a woman and her two children.[199]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it had launched a drone strike on a "vital target" in Eilat.[200][201][202]
  • Hezbollah said it had targeted an IDF intelligence base in the suburbs of Tel Aviv.[203]
  • The IDF launched strikes on area in Tyre centered around two buildings.[204] The IDF said it had targeted Hezbollah command and control complexes, including the headquarters of the Southern Front Unit used to attack Israeli citizens and forces without offering evidence.[205]
  • Wafa reported that an Israeli strike on a "civilian vehicle" travelling through Salah al-Din Street, south of Deir el-Balah, killed two people.[206]
  • An armed Palestinian man was killed and another was moderately injured by Israeli forces in the West Bank.[207]
  • The IDF said it had killed three Hezbollah sector commanders and 70 other Hezbollah militants.[208] It also claimed to have killed Khalil Muhammad Amhaz, an expert in the Hezbollah air unit responsible for designing its kamikaze drones and reconnaissance drones.[209]
  • An Israeli air strike on a vehicle in Nabatieh killed an Iranian medic.[210]
  • Approximately 135 rockets and five drones were launched from Lebanon towards Israel.[211][212]
  • An Israeli strike in northern Gaza City killed three people including a woman and her two children and injured six others.[213]
  • An Israeli drone struck a clearly marked UNRWA vehicle in southern Deir el-Balah, killing two people including an UNRWA employee and injuring four others.[213][214]
  • The WHO announced that polio vaccination for children in northern Gaza was postponed due to Israeli bombardment, mass displacement and lack of access.[215]
  • Gholamreza Jalali, the head of Iran's National Organization for Passive Defense said that Israeli cyberattacks against Iranian interests are continuing, but they are facing a "layer-by-layer" defence strategy that have kept them at bay.[216]
  • The IDF claimed to have arrested over 150 Palestinian fighters from Jabalia.[217]
  • Israeli settlers destroyed over 15 Palestinian-owned residential structures in the Jurat al-Kheil community east of Sa'ir and confiscated the belongings of its residents.[218]
  • A man was moderately injured by shrapnel in Nahariya during a Hezbollah barrage of 25 rockets.[219]
  • Hezbollah said it had launched a rocket strike targeting Israeli soldiers in Misgav Am.[220]
  • The Gaza Government Media Office announced that more than 770 Palestinians were killed and over 1,000 were injured since the start of the Siege of Jabalia. It also said that over 200 civilians, including women, had been "kidnapped".[221]
  • Hamas posted a video of its fighters destroying an Israeli Merkava tank using rockets in the Tall az-Zaatar neighbourhood, east of Jabalia. It also claimed to have fired 114mm "Rajum" rockets at an Israeli command-and-control site along the Netzarim Corridor. It also reported that a D9 IDF bulldozer struck a landmine in as-Saftawi in northern Gaza and another bulldozer was targeted using an antiarmour shell and an explosive device in the al-Faluja neighbourhood of Jabalia.[222]
  • An Israeli drone shot and killed the director of the municipal police of the northern Gaza Strip, Mazen al-Kahlout, near the al-Yaman al-Saeed Hospital in Jabalia.[223]
  • Spain's Defense Ministry said it had suspended all contracts to buy weapons from Israel since October 7, 2023, with the exception of maintenance work.[224]
  • Hezbollah said its fighters had launched kamikaze drones containing explosives towards an IDF base south of Haifa.[225]
  • Wafa reported that an Israeli air strike in the Tal al-Hawa neighbourhood in southwestern Gaza City killed four Palestinian civilians and wounded several others.[226]
  • The al-Qassam Brigades said they had attacked an IDF command centre in northern Gaza using rockets and engaged Israeli soldiers inside using small-arms fire. They claimed to have killed and wounded some Israeli soldiers and said their fighters had monitored the landing of two helicopters sent for evacuation.[227]
  • The IDF accused six Al Jazeera journalists in northern Gaza of being militants. Al Jazeera denied the claim.[228][229]
  • Hezbollah said that it had forced Israeli soldiers to retreat when they attempted to "infiltrate" from the outskirts of Aitarun.[230]
  • Hezbollah claimed that it had killed over 70 Israeli soldiers.[231]
  • Israeli prime minister Benjamin Netanyahu claimed that Hezbollah had prepared an "invasion" of Israel.[232]
  • Four projectiles were launched from Lebanon towards central Israel, three of which were intercepted or hit open areas.[233] Hezbollah later claimed that it had struck a military industries company in the suburbs of Tel Aviv using rockets.[234][235]
  • An Israeli airstrike destroyed an office of the Hezbollah-linked broadcaster Al Mayadeen in Beirut, killing one person and injuring five others.[236][237]
  • A Palestinian was lightly injured either by a rocket fired from Lebanon or an Israeli interceptor missile in Ras Atiya.[238]
  • The UN said that two water stations are not operating in northern Gaza due to lack of fuel and that fuel deliveries are being denied by Israeli authorities.[239]
  • The Gaza civil defence said that three of their rescuers were injured in a "targeted strike" which aimed to force them out of the Jabalia refugee camp. Later, they said that their northern Gaza operations were temporarily stopped after the IDF detained five staff members and destroyed their only fire truck. The Gaza City municipality said that an Israeli strike killed two of its workers and injured three others.[240]
  • Israeli forces conducted three raids on the town of Khiam in southern Lebanon.[241]
  • Four reservists of the Carmeli Brigade's 222nd Battalion were killed and six others were injured, three seriously, after they were ambushed by Hezbollah fighters with grenades in southern Lebanon.[242]

24 October

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 55 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 42,847.[243][a]
  • The Lebanese government reported that at least 19 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon in the past 24 hours.[244]
  • Hezbollah launched approximately 120 rockets towards Israel.[245]
  • The Syrian defence ministry and SANA reported that Israeli strikes on a residential building in Kafr Sousa and a military site in Homs Governorate killed a soldier and wounded seven others.[246]
  • An Israeli strike during the evacuation of injured people from the outskirts of Yater killed three Lebanese soldiers, including an officer.[247]
  • Clashes were reported with Palestinian armed groups during an IDF raid in the Balata refugee camp.[248]
  • The IAF said it had killed dozens of militants over the past day, struck over 160 Hezbollah targets including launchers, military buildings and military infrastructure throughout Lebanon and "eliminated" several militant squads using aerial strikes. The IDF also claimed its 98th division had located ammunition depots containing hundreds of antitank missiles and mortar bombs.[249]
  • The IDF said that its Division 162 had killed dozens of militants and destroyed dozens of militant infrastructure in the Jabalia refugee camp since the start of the Second battle of Jabalia.[250]
  • An Israeli air strike hit a house in the Jabalia refugee camp killing a woman and her child.[251]
  • The IDF said it had struck several Hezbollah weapons storage facilities and weapons factories in its overnight strikes in Dahieh.[252]
  • More than 150 Palestinians were detained in northern Gaza and taken to Israel.[253]
  • IRGC chief Hossein Salami claimed that THAAD systems will not be enough if Israel prompts an Iranian attack by attacking Iran.[254]
  • Gaza civil defence said that Israeli forces ordered its crews to evacuate from north Gaza and move to the Indonesian hospital. Five of its vehicles were attacked in Beit Lahia.[255]
  • Rocket shrapnel moderately injured two people and lightly injured two others in the Western Galilee. Hezbollah claimed multiple strikes including launching rockets towards Safed and Nahariya and also targeted the Zevulon military industries base north of Haifa with rockets.[256]
  • Israel asked approximately 25 towns in the Upper Galilee to limit their movement, avoid gatherings and stay in the vicinity of protected zones.[257]
  • Israeli missile strikes on the Shuhadaa al-Nuseirat school serving as a shelter for displaced families in the Nuseirat refugee camp killed at least 18 Palestinians, including children, women, elderly people and injured at least 52 others.[258][259][260] The IDF said it had targeted Hamas militants operating inside a command and control centre in the area.[261]
  • An Israeli strike on a car in the vicinity of Aley killed at least one person.[262]
  • The IDF arrested at least 18 people including a journalist from the West Bank. During an IDF raid in Hebron, Palestinian houses were vandalised and damaged and some Palestinians were used as human shields.[263]
  • Hamas said it is engaged in intense efforts to thwart implementation of the General's Plan in northern Gaza.[264]
  • Hezbollah claimed to have killed Israeli soldiers after a firefight in Ayta ash Shab, destroyed a Merkava tank which tried to provide support and hit another Merkava. It also claimed multiple rocket strikes targeting a gathering of Israeli soldiers in Misgav Am and Manara, Kiryat Shmona, and a logistical base affiliated with the IDF Northern Command between Nahariya and Acre.[265]
  • Hezbollah fired five rockets at Karmiel, with shrapnel from an intercepted rocket lightly injuring an elderly man.[266] It also claimed that it had forced Israeli soldiers advancing in the vicinity of Odaisseh to retreat following clashes.[267]
  • Over 770 people were killed since the start of the Second battle of Jabalia. Gaza Civil Defense accused that the IDF had threatened to "bomb and kill" its crews in northern Gaza.[268]
  • Hezbollah said its fighters had struck a Merkava tank to the northwest of Odaisseh using a guided missile. It also claimed it had inflicted casualties and injuries on the Israeli crew.[269]
  • A Gaza civil defence worker said that Israeli forces killed some people around Kamal Edwan Hospital and arrested most of its surgeons. The director of the hospital said that their intensive care unit was severely damaged by Israeli tank shelling.[270][271]
  • Hezbollah said it had destroyed an IDF tank in Aita al-Shaab using a guided missile and claimed they had killed and injured its crew. It also said its fighters had engaged in intense clashes at "point-blank range" with assault weapons and rocket-propelled grenades against IDF vehicles in Aita al-Shaab.[272]
  • An IDF attack destroyed at least 10 residential buildings in the al-Hawja residential area inside the Jabalia refugee camp. According to an assessment by Gaza Civil Defense, it was estimated that 150 people including women and children were either killed or injured.[273]
  • Two Israeli officers were seriously injured in separate incidents in southern Lebanon. In a third incident, a commander of the Oketz Unit was killed and a reservist from the 55th Paratroopers Brigade's 7155th Battalion was seriously injured during a clash with Hezbollah members.[242][274]
  • Israeli strikes hit the southern suburbs of Beirut.[275]
  • Israeli artillery fire in Khan Yunis killed two Palestinians and injured 20 others including women and children.[276]
  • The IDF killed UNRWA employee Muhammad Abu Atiwi. It alleged that he was a Hamas commander and was responsible for killing and kidnapping Israeli civilians during the October 7 attack without providing evidence.[277]
  • A projectile was launched from the "east" towards Israel.[278] The Islamic Resistance in Iraq released a video to announce that it had launched a drone at a "vital target" in Eilat.[279]
  • Five reservists of the IDF's 8th Armored Brigade's 89th Battalion, including its deputy commander, were killed and 24 others were injured, four seriously, when a Hezbollah rocket struck a building in southern Lebanon.[280][281][282]
  • An Israeli strike in Khan Yunis killed an MSF employee.[283]

25 October

  • The Lebanese Health Ministry reported that at least 41 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon in the past 24 hours.[284]
  • Israeli forces bombed a house belonging to the Farra family in Qizan an-Najjar, east of Khan Yunis, killing three people and injuring five more.[285]
  • An apparent Israeli targeted strike on a compound where journalists were housed in villas in Hasbaiyya killed three journalists. Two of them were staff members of the Hezbollah linked news television channel Al Mayadeen, and the third person killed was a staff member of the Hezbollah linked television station Al-Manar TV. Three others were injured.[286][287][288]
  • An Israeli strike on an oxygen station in the Kamal Adwan Hospital in Beit Lahia reportedly killed a number of infants and children due to a lack of oxygen.[289][290]
  • Israeli strikes on a multiple residential structures in the al-Manara area, south of Khan Yunis, killed at least 38 people including 14 children.[291][292]
  • The IDF claimed that its fighter jets had killed Abbas Adnan Maslam, a Redwan force commander in Aitaroun responsible for the execution of many shooting plans targeting the IDF and settlements in northern Israel. It also claimed it had struck approximately 200 militant targets in Lebanon and killed a number of militants from the ground and air in Gaza over the past day.[293]
  • The IDF carried out mass arrests of men from the Kamal Edwan Hospital, the arrested were taken to an unknown area for interrogation.[294] Among those taken was 18-year-old Palestinian activist and media worker Abdul Rahman "Aboud" Batah.[295]
  • Five Israeli soldiers were killed during combat in southern Lebanon one day prior.[280]
  • Israeli soldiers stationed at al-Kassara junction, south of Hebron shot and injured a 16-year-old boy on his foot.[296]
  • Lebanese health minister Firass Abiad said that 163 rescuers and health workers were killed and 273 others were injured in Lebanon since the start of Israel-Hezbollah conflict.[297]
  • The Qassam Brigades reported that it carried out a "complex ambush" by hitting two personnel carriers and an IDF bulldozer east of Jabalia. It also reported that it sniped an Israeli soldier north of the Jabalia refugee camp.[298]
  • An Israeli soldier was seriously injured in southern Lebanon.[281]
  • An Israeli airstrike disabled the Qaa crossing on the Lebanon–Syria border.[299]
  • Israeli combat engineers from the Carmeli Brigade destroyed two Hezbollah tunnels in southern Lebanon.[300]
  • Israeli soldiers raided multiple houses in 'Anata, causing damage to property. Wafa reported that Israeli soldiers used the house of a resident as a temporary military outpost.[301]
  • Hezbollah claimed that it inflicted casualties on Israeli forces advancing towards Marwahin with anti-armour guided missiles. It added that it struck a Merkava tank with another guided missile and claimed that it killed and injured its crew. It said that it fired multiple rocket barrages at Israeli settlements along the border and said that it targeted an IDF base south of Haifa with missiles.[302]
  • An Israeli strike on Al-Shati refugee camp killed and injured at least 20 people.[303]
  • A leaked UNIFIL report accused the IDF of attacking UN positions 12 times. It also accused the IDF of using white phosphorus against peacekeepers.[304]
  • A Hezbollah rocket attack in Shomera injured six Israeli soldiers.[305][306]
  • The IDF said that it struck Hezbollah weapons production facilities, an intelligence headquarters and air defence capabilities in its air strikes in Beirut.[307]
  • Hezbollah fired 30 rockets targeting Karmiel.[308] Two civilians were killed and seven others were injured, one critically and one seriously, when a rocket hit a market in the nearby city of Majd al-Krum.[309]
  • Three Israeli soldiers were killed while fighting in northern Gaza, bringing the IDF's death toll in the Gaza Strip to 361.[310]
  • Hezbollah said that it fired a rocket salvo towards Safed. It also said that it launched an air strike using a swarm of explosives containing drones towards an IDF base situated in the east of the same area.[311]
  • Hezbollah claimed that it inflicted injuries by targeting an Israeli force of 12 soldiers using a guided missile in the outskirts of Odaisseh. It also said that it struck a Hummer IDF vehicle with four soldiers.[312]
  • Gaza Civil Defense said that Israeli drone strikes on a group of Palestinians waiting for receiving aid in the vicinity of Shati refugee camp killed 12 people and injured several others.[313]
  • Hezbollah fired a total of 65 rockets at northern Israel throughout the day.[314]

26 October

  • The Lebanese Health Ministry reported that at least 19 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon one day prior.[315]
  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 77 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 48 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 42,924.[316][a]
  • The IDF carried out airstrikes in Iran in response to its attacks against Israel.[317][318] An Iranian civilian and four Iranian soldiers were killed in the strikes.[319][320]
  • Israeli soldiers reportedly used the parents of a Palestinian suspect in the as-Salam neighbourhood in the vicinity of Nur Shams refugee camp as human shields to force him to surrender.[321]
  • The IDF said that its fighter jets struck 70 Hezbollah targets including antitank positions, military buildings, ammunition depots and operatives in the past 24 hours. It also released a footage of its soldiers operating in southern Lebanon attacking Hezbollah operatives and retrieving weapons. A drone containing explosives was launched from Lebanon towards northern Israel.[322]
  • Two drones were launched from Lebanon towards Israel.[323]
  • The NNA reported that the IDF blew up houses in Odaisseh.[324]
  • Hezbollah said that it targeted the Tel Nof Airbase south of Tel Aviv with drone strikes. It said that it launched a rocket salvo towards Israeli soldiers on the outskirts of Aita al-Shaab.[325][326]
  • The al-Qassam Brigades said that its fighters blew up a house where Israeli soldiers were located, killing and injuring some of them. It also added that it targeted two tanks north of the Jabalia refugee camp.[327]
  • Hezbollah said that its rocket salvo targeted the Meishar base, allegedly an intelligence headquarters for northern Israel.[326]
  • The IDF detained 15 people including children from the West Bank. It reportedly physically assaulted and threatened detainees and caused significant property damage.[328]
  • An Israeli bombardment in Jabalia refugee camp killed the child of the hospital director.[329] Israeli forces reportedly caused widespread damage to the pharmaceutical warehouse and the ICU of the Kamal Adwan Hospital.[330] COGAT said that several patients and their escorts were evacuated from the hospital with the help of UNICEF and WHO, while hospital was given fuel, blood units and medical equipment. The IDF said that it operated in the hospital due to intelligence regarding the presence of militants and militant infrastructure.[331] The Palestinian Health Ministry said that Israeli forces arrested all male medical staff and a number of wounded and sick from the hospital and led them to unknown areas for interrogation. Women were detained in one of its rooms without water or food.[332][333] Three staff members were injured after Israeli soldiers opened fire.[334]
  • Hezbollah launched about 80 projectiles towards Israel.[335]
  • The IDF said that it killed a Hamas commander who was the leader of Hamas operations in Tulkarm.[336]
  • Hezbollah said that it launched a rocket salvo towards five residential areas in northern Israel including the outskirts of Krayot.[337]
  • An Israeli airstrike on a health centre in Bazouriyeh killed a paramedic affiliated with the Hezbollah-affiliated Islamic Health Committee and injured five others including three paramedics from Islamic Health Committee.[338]
  • Microsoft fired two employees who organised an unapproved protest at its headquarters in Redmond for Palestinians killed in Gaza.[339]
  • Wafa reported that Israeli forces targeted al-Shahayda area north of Abasan al-Kabira, resulting in several deaths among civilians.[340]
  • Israeli forces shot and killed a Palestinian in the village of Azzun Al Atmeh, south of Qalqilyia.[341]
  • The IDF eased some restrictions for residents in areas of northern Israel.[342]
  • An Israeli strike on a residential area in Beit Lahia killed at least 35 Palestinians.[343]
  • Hezbollah urged residents of at least 25 communities in northern Israel and a few settlements in Golan Heights to evacuate, saying that those places have become "legitimate military targets" after stationing of Israeli forces.[344][345]
  • The IDF issued evacuation warnings for residents of several buildings in the Burj al-Barajneh and Hadath areas in the southern suburbs of Beirut.[346]
  • An elderly woman died after tripping on stairs while evacuating to a bomb shelter in Beit HaEmek.[347]
  • Five soldiers of the Alon Brigade, including its rabbi, and three Hezbollah fighters were killed during a battle in southern Lebanon, increasing the IDF death toll in the invasion of Lebanon to 37. Fourteen other soldiers were injured in the same incident, four of them seriously.[348][349][350]

27 October

  • Israeli forces bombed a building that housed displaced people in Beit Lahia, killing ten people.[351]
  • Israeli forces attacked the Salah al-Din School in Gaza City, killing one person and injuring more. The IDF said that it targeted Hamas fighters who operated a command and control complex in the building without providing evidence.[352]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq claimed a drone strike on a "viral target" in the occupied Golan Heights, during the time of the attacks sirens were set off in the illegal Kidmat Tsvi settlement.[353]
  • Hezbollah said that it launched a rocket salvo towards Kiryat Shmona.[354][355]
  • Al Jazeera reported that Israeli bombardment on homes in az-Zarqa area in the vicinity of Jabalia, killed many people.[356]
  • Two drones launched from Lebanon entered Israel.[357]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it launched drone strikes on a "vital target" in the Golan Heights and Eilat.[358]
  • The IDF said that its fighter jets struck Hezbollah weapons warehouses and sites used for the manufacturing and maintenance of weapons in Dahieh without providing evidence. It also claimed to have killed 70 Hezbollah fighters and struck over 120 Hezbollah positions.[359]
  • A drone launched from Lebanon hit the roof of a factory manufacturing aviation components in the industrial area of Bar-Lev in Karmiel, injuring two people.[360] Hezbollah said that its drone strike targeted the "Yudifat military industries company" southwest of Acre.[361]
  • Iran's Supreme Leader Ali Khamenei said Iran's power should be demonstrated to Israel.[318]
  • A truck rammed into a bus stop in Aharon Yariv Boulevard in Ramat HaSharon, killing one person and injuring 40 others. The truck driver was shot and killed.[362]
  • Hezbollah claimed that its operatives killed and injured Israeli soldiers by hitting an Israeli infantry group advancing in Hula with a guided missile.[361]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents of 14 towns and villages in southern Lebanon to move to the north of the Awali river.[363]
  • Hezbollah said that it launched four more strikes on IDF and claimed that its drones killed and wounded Israeli soldiers in the vicinity of Manara and Marj IDF site.[364]
  • Approximately 75 rockets were launched from Lebanon towards northern Israel. One rocket hit the ground injuring three people in Tamra, including a woman who was critically injured.[365]
  • The IDF said that it shot dead a Palestinian who tried to carry out a ramming and stabbing attack targeting soldiers in the vicinity of Hizma.[366]
  • An Israeli air strike on UN run Asmaa school sheltering displaced families in Al-Shati refugee camp killed at least 11 people including at least two children and three journalists and injured several others.[367][368][369] Those journalists worked for Hamas-affiliated media outlets. The IDF said it targeted Hamas operatives including an al-Qassam Brigades cell commander and three other militants in a command and control center embedded in the compound.[368]
  • The IDF said that it killed the commander of Hezbollah's Bint Jbeil division and his successor in two separate airstrikes within 24 hours.[370]
  • An Israeli airstrike in Sidon killed nine people and injured 25 others.[371][372][373]
  • A soldier from the Givati Brigade's Rotem Battalion died from wounds sustained during combat in northern Gaza on 18 October, increasing the IDF death toll in the Gaza Strip to 362.[350]
  • Hezbollah said that its air defence units forced back Israeli warplanes using surface-to-air missiles above western Lebanon.[374]
  • An Israeli air strike on a rescue center in Ain Baal killed seven people including a nurse and three paramedics and injured 24 others.[375]
  • A group of Israeli settlers gathered at the bypass road in the vicinity of the bridge connecting Madama and Burin and attacked the vehicles of Palestinian residents.[376]
  • Israeli strikes in Gaza killed two more reporters.[377]
  • Two Palestinian women were injured by Israeli settlers in Deir Sharaf.[378]

28 October

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 96 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 48 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,020.[379][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry reported that at least 38 people were killed and 124 others were injured in Israeli attacks in Lebanon one day prior.[380]
  • Israeli strikes on at least five homes in Beit Lahia trapped at least a dozen Palestinians under the rubble.[367]
  • The Jenin Battalion claimed that it repelled Israeli soldiers from Jenin.[381]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it targeted an IDF target in northern Israel with drones.[382]
  • The IDF continued air and ground operations in Jabalia, killing dozens of fighters. It claimed that it destroyed underground tunnels and retrieved several weapons. It said that operations also continued in Rafah, killing fighters and destroying their infrastructure. Its soldiers located fighters in a nearby destroyed structure and killed them in cooperation with the IAF in one incident. It also said it killed a number of fighters and destroyed a building used by them in its operation in central Gaza.[383]
  • Mossad director David Barnea held negotiations with the Qatari government.[384]
  • The Gaza Health Ministry said that the IDF arrested and deported all medical staff except a pediatrician from the Kamal Edwan Hospital.[385]
  • Wafa reported that an Israeli drone shot dead a child in Maghazi refugee camp and an artillery strikes in Bureij refugee camp killed two civilians and wounded several others.[386]
  • There were unconfirmed reports that two IDF officers and a number of Israeli soldiers were killed in Lebanon. The IDF said that over 1200 Hezbollah militants were killed since the start of its ground operation in Lebanon and claimed that Hezbollah maintained only 30% of the rockets it initially had before the conflict.[387][388]
  • A major serving as a company commander in the IDF's 52nd Battalion (part of the 401st Armored Brigade) died from injuries suffered during combat in northern Gaza on 19 October.[389][390]
  • The IDF said that it arrested almost 100 Hamas militants from Kamal Adwan Hospital and some of them participated in the October 7 attack. It also claimed that it found weapons, funds and intelligence documents in the hospital and surrounding area.[391][392]
  • In Jerusalem, a march and a hand-holding protest in support of Israel was held at the Western Wall. It was organized by the Indigenous Embassy Jerusalem, a nonprofit co-headed by Alfred Ngaro and founded in 2024 to change the "false narrative" that "paints the Jews as the foreign colonizers who have dispossessed the indigenous Palestinians". About 60 members of various Indigenous cultures from around the world participated. They said they affirm the God-given right of the people of Israel to the land, and compared the suffering of Jews in the state of Israel to the suffering of Indigenous nations.[393]
  • An Israeli airstrike in Tyre killed seven people and injured 17 others.[394][395]
  • Sinjil municipality said that Israeli settlers set fire to Palestinian land.[396]
  • Hezbollah claimed that a drone hit the Yudifat Military Industries Company southeast of Acre.[397]
  • Hezbollah claimed that it inflicted casualties and injuries among Israeli soldiers by ambushing two IDF vehicles advancing to the Tal Nahas area on the outskirts of Kafr Kila using machine guns and rockets.[398]
  • About 115 projectiles were launched by Hezbollah from Lebanon towards Israel.[399]
  • At least 60 people including at least two children were killed in Israeli airstrikes in the Baalbek area.[400]
  • Two people were killed in an Israeli airstrike on a vehicle in Al-Nizariyah, on the Syrian-Lebanese border.[401]
  • The Israeli Knesset passed legislation designating UNRWA as a "terrorist organization", which will take effect "within 90 days".[402][403]
  • The Houthis said that it targeted the ships SC Montrship using two drones and Maersk Kowloon using a missile in the Arabian Sea. It also said that it targeted the ship Motaro using ballistic missiles in the Red Sea and the Bab-el-Mandeb.[404]
  • The Gaza Health Ministry accused Israeli forces of sabotaging the polio vaccination campaign in northern Gaza and Gaza City.[405]

29 October

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 41 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,061.[406][a]
  • An Israeli air strike in central az-Zawayda killed 10 people.[407]
  • At least 109 Palestinians including children and women were killed and dozens of others were injured after an Israeli airstrike destroyed a five-story residential building housing displaced people in Beit Lahia.[408][409][410]
  • The Houthis said that it launched drones towards an industrial zone in Ashkelon.[411]
  • Hezbollah elected Naim Qassem as its new secretary-general.[412]
  • Israeli shelling in al-Bureij refugee camp killed a Palestinian woman and her two sons.[413]
  • Hezbollah fired 50 rockets at Ma'alot-Tarshiha, killing one person.[414]
  • The IDF said that it destroyed a Hezbollah underground command centre which was built eight metres underground and another bunker used to store half a tonne of explosives during its ground operations in southern Lebanon.[415]
  • A drone from Lebanon hit a bridge at the Nahariya railway station. A second drone was intercepted over the Upper Galilee.[414]
  • Four Israeli soldiers were killed in northern Gaza, increasing the IDF death toll in the Gaza Strip to 367.[416]
  • The Arab Center for the Advancement of Social Media said that at least 50 percent of telecommunications infrastructure in Gaza was destroyed.[417]
  • Eight Austrian peacekeepers were slightly injured when a Hezbollah rocket hit the UNIFIL headquarters in Camp Naqoura, in the vicinity of the Israeli border.[418][419]
  • Spain canceled a contract to buy police ammunition from an Israeli firm.[420]
  • Nine people were killed and a girl was trapped under rubble in an Israeli airstrike in Haret Saida, southeast of Sidon.[421][422]
  • Another Israeli air strike on a residential area in Beit Lahia killed at least 19 people.[423][424]
  • Israeli defence minister Yoav Gallant claimed that Hezbollah maintained only 20% of the rockets and missiles it initially had before the conflict.[425] Hezbollah denied the claim.[426]
  • Two Palestinians were injured apparently by an Israeli settler while harvesting olives in the vicinity of Havat Gilad.[427]
  • The IDF announced that Hezbollah's commander in Ayta ash Shab was captured by Israeli forces two weeks prior.[428]
  • A soldier of the 7155th battalion of the 55th Paratroopers Brigade died of wounds sustained fighting Hezbollah in southern Lebanon on 24 October, increasing the IDF death toll in the invasion of Lebanon to 42.[429]
  • Israeli forces detained three people, including two children from Husan.[430]
  • Israeli tanks reportedly entered the outskirts of Khiam following a wave of heavy air attacks on the village. Hezbollah claimed that it destroyed two tanks with guided missiles and attacked Israeli troops with artillery and rockets southwest of the village.[431]
  • An Israeli airstrike in Sarafand killed 10 people and injured 21 others, while a strike near Sidon killed six and injured 37.[432][433]
  • Hezbollah fired approximately 75 rockets at northern Israel throughout the day.[434]

30 October

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 102 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,163.[435][a]
  • At least 77 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon in the past 24 hours.[436]
  • The IDF said that it carried out a "precise" strike on militants in the Khan Yunis "humanitarian zone".[437]
  • The Quds News Network and the Palestinian Information Center reported that an Israeli air strike on a house in the Sheikh Nasser area of Khan Yunis killed three people, including a woman and her children.[438]
  • Clashes were reported between Israeli forces and Palestinian fighters in Burqa and the Balata refugee camp.[439]
  • The IDF said that it struck over 100 targets in Lebanon including Hezbollah rocket launchers and claimed that it killed dozens of militants one day prior.[440]
  • An overnight drone attack apparently from Iraq caused minor damage to an aviation factory in Nahariya.[441][442]
  • Israeli settlers cut down and uprooted dozens of olive trees near Qaryut next to the Israeli settlement of Eli.[443]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents of at least eight towns in southern Lebanon to move to the north of the Awali River.[444] Evacuation orders were also issued for residents of Baalbek, Ain Bourday and Douris,[445] after which Israeli fighter jets launched a series of strikes on the al-Asira area of Baalbek, Iaat, Douris and surrounding areas.[446][447]
  • An Israeli drone strike hit a car in the Araya area of Baabda District.[448]
  • Shrapnel from a Hezbollah rocket attack near Metula injured two farmworkers, one seriously.[449]
  • The IDF announced that it killed Mustafa Ahmad Shahadi, the Redwan Force's deputy commander, in an airstrike in Nabatieh.[450]
  • Israeli airstrikes on one of the main markets in Beit Lahia killed 10 Palestinians and injured 20 others.[451]
  • An Israeli strike hit a car in the eastern area of Maghazi refugee camp killing three Palestinians including a woman and injured several others.[451]
  • Hezbollah launched at least 60 projectiles from Lebanon towards Israel.[452]
  • Israeli airstrikes in Sohmor killed 11 people and injured 15 others.[453]
  • The IDF said that it struck fuel depots situated in military complexes of logistical empowerment unit of Hezbollah in Bekaa.[454]
  • Hezbollah said that it struck the Ein Shemer Airfield, the Eliakim camp and Shraga base north of Acre with rockets and drones.[455]
  • Iran said that it killed a separatist linked to Israel.[456]
  • Glia said that Israel revoked a ban on its medical teams entering Gaza.[457]
  • The IDF announced a new division for operating on the border with Jordan.[458]
  • A Hezbollah drone attack injured two people in Hadera.[459]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that Israeli strikes killed 19 people, including eight women, in two towns in Baalbek District.[460]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it targeted a "vital target" in the Golan Heights using drones.[461]
  • A Katyusha rocket targeting Israel hit the Irish peacekeeping base Camp Shamrock in southern Lebanon, causing minor damage.[462]

31 October

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 41 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,204.[463][a]
  • At least 45 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon in the past 24 hours.[464]
  • Hezbollah-affiliated al-Manar reported that a drone launched from Lebanon hit its target in Nahariya.[465]
  • Hamas confirmed the death of Hussam Bassam Yousef Malah, a "prominent" Hamas leader in an Israeli undercover operation in Tulkarm. The IDF accused him and two other men recently killed by Israeli forces of planning attacks.[466]
  • The IDF laid siege to Nur Shams refugee camp and carried out a drone strike on a square, killing two people including a child and triggering clashes with Palestinian fighters.[467][468]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it launched drone strikes on "vital" targets in the Golan Heights and in northern Israel and an IDF site in southern Israel.[469]
  • Houthi media reported an US and British airstrike in the vicinity of Hodeidah University.[470]
  • The IDF claimed that its fighter jets struck approximately 150 Hamas linked targets in Gaza and Hezbollah-linked targets in Lebanon including Hezbollah headquarters and rocket launchers. It said that it launched dozens of strikes in central and northern Gaza and a Hezbollah unit launched a missile towards one of its fighter jets above an area north of Tyre and it responded by destroying the site. It also said that it continued its ground operations in southern Lebanon, destroying militant infrastructures and striking antitank squads.[471]
  • Israeli soldiers continued blowing up entire villages in southern Lebanon ostensibly for links to militant activity.[471]
  • Iran said that it foiled an attack by a separatist group it accused of links with Israel.[472]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for 10 towns and villages in southern Lebanon including Al-Hawsh, Borgholiyeh and Ansar.[473] Later, a series of Israeli airstrikes struck the Al-Hawsh area.[474]
  • The Gaza Health Ministry said that Israeli forces struck the third floor of the Kamal Adwan Hospital containing medicine and medical supplies.[475]
  • Israeli police arrested an Israeli couple on suspicion of spying for Iran.[476]
  • Israeli forces launched airstrikes in Baalbek District, killing eight people, including two children.[477]
  • Israeli authorities moved to seize 64 dunams of Palestinian land from Umm Tuba.[478]
  • SANA reported that Israeli strikes hit a number of residential buildings in Al-Qusayr, causing "material damage" to its industrial zone and some of its residential neighbourhoods killing 10 people, including civilians.[479][480] The IDF said that it struck Hezbollah command centers and weapon depots.[481]
  • A Hezbollah barrage of two rockets hit an apple orchard near Metula, killing five agricultural workers including four Thai nationals and seriously injuring one.[482][483]
  • An Israeli airstrike on an Al-Risala Health Ambulance Association vehicle in Zefta killed a paramedic and wounded two others.[484]
  • Israeli shelling hit a group of people in the vicinity of the al-Sahaba intersection at the Daraj neighbourhood in Gaza City, killing four people, including a child and injured several others.[485]
  • The Global Youth Movement called for a global hunger strike starting on 1 November demanding the end of the siege in Gaza, stopping forced displacement of Palestinians and bringing humanitarian aid to northern Gaza and said that its strike will continue until its demands are met.[486]
  • Israeli strikes killed five other medics and injured two others.[487]
  • Hezbollah fired 25 projectiles at the Haifa area. Two people were killed and a third was lightly injured near Kiryat Ata.[488][489]
  • Two drones were launched from the east towards Israel.[490]
  • An Israeli strike hit two homes in the vicinity of the Nuseirat refugee camp, killing 16 people.[491]

November 2024

1 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 55 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,259.[492][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 30 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon in the past 24 hours.[493]
  • The IDF issued two evacuation orders for residents of Haret Hreik, Bourj el-Barajneh, and Ghobeiry after which a series of Israeli strikes hit the areas.[494]
  • Two drones were launched from the east towards Israel.[495]
  • The IDF issued two other evacuation orders for residents of three neighbourhoods of Dahieh and an area referred to as the "pond enclosure" after which Israeli strikes hit the areas, killing two people and injuring four others.[496][497]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it launched three drones towards "vital targets" in southern Israel and a drone towards a "vital target" in the Golan Heights.[498]
  • Clashes were reported between IDF and Palestinian fighters in Nablus.[499]
  • A UAV launched towards Israel was intercepted in Syria.[500]
  • Israeli bombardment in Deir Al-Balah, the Nuseirat refugee camp and Al-Zawayda killed 47 Palestinians mostly children and women and injured dozens of people.[501]
  • The IDF said that it killed three gunmen during a raid in Tulkarm.[502]
  • A platoon commander from the Givati Brigade died from injuries sustained when he was hit by weaponry which detonated inside a building in Rafah on September 17.[503]
  • An Israeli strike on Palestinians was reported in a market in the Sheikh Radwan area, west of Gaza City. A child was also injured in the strike.[504]
  • Another Israeli strike on the entrance of a school serving as shelter for displaced people in the Nuseirat refugee camp killed at least 14 Palestinians.[505]
  • An Israeli strike on a car in Khan Yunis killed 10 people.[505]
  • An Israeli airstrike on a home in Taraya killed two people including a woman and injured four others.[506]
  • A Hezbollah rocket barrage of approximately 30 rockets was launched towards Galilee, causing several injuries.[507]
  • Hezbollah claimed to have hit Karmiel and Ma'alot-Tarshiha.[508]
  • An Israeli strike near Firas market in Gaza City killed at least three people including journalist Bilal Rajab and wounded several.[509]
  • Wafa reported that armed Israeli settlers from Bat Ayin, backed by Israeli soldiers attacked Palestinian houses in the Deir al-Nil area of Surif and shot at them.[510]
  • The IDF claimed to have killed senior Hamas official Izz al-Din Kassab in an airstrike in Khan Yunis, saying that he was one of the last high-ranking members of Hamas responsible for coordinating with other groups in Gaza.[511]
  • Israeli police arrested several suspects for the alleged leak of classified intelligence from the prime minister's office containing sensitive information on the Gaza war.[512]
  • An Israeli airstrike in Nuseirat refugee camp killed four people, including three children.[505]
  • Two Israeli strikes on buildings in northern Gaza killed 84 Palestinians, including over 50 children.[513]
  • Israeli soldiers prevented Palestinian farmers from harvesting olives in Deir Istiya.[514]
  • An Israeli airstrike hit a border crossing on the Lebanon–Syria border, forcing it to close.[515]
  • Israeli airstrikes in Baalbek-Hermel Governorate killed 52 people and injured 72 others.[516]
  • An Israeli airstrike on a home in Amhaz killed at least 12 people and injured several others.[517][518]
  • Israeli naval forces reportedly captured Hezbollah official Imad Amhaz during a raid in Batroun, south of Tripoli.[519]
  • The IDF announced that the commander of Hezbollah's coastal unit and the commander of the unit's artillery division were killed in an airstrike in Tyre.[520]

2 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 55 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,314.[521][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 71 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon a day prior.[522]
  • Clashes were reported between the IDF and the Al-Aqsa Martyrs Brigades during a raid in Jaba.[523]
  • Rockets launched from Lebanon injured at least 19 people in Hod HaSharon.[524]
  • 11 people were injured in a Hezbollah rocket attack on a building in Tira.[525]
  • Northern Command commander Ori Gordin was slightly wounded along with several Israeli soldiers after their vehicle overturned during a patrol in Lebanon.[526]
  • Al Jazeera Arabic reported that Israeli forces destroyed residential buildings north of the Nuseirat refugee camp.[527]
  • Al Jazeera reported that three civilians were killed after an Israeli drone strike in as-Saftawi, North Gaza Governorate.[528]
  • Wafa reported that armed Israeli settlers attacked Palestinian olive pickers in Khalat al-Haramiya, west of Salfit.[529]
  • Four drones were launched by Islamic Resistance in Iraq towards Israel, claiming that it targeted sites in Eilat.[530][531]
  • An Israeli strike on a home north of the Nuseirat camp killed Palestinian journalist Baraa Ali Daghish.[532]
  • Hezbollah claimed to target Yesod HaMa’ala, Bar Yohai, Birya,[533] Palmachim Airbase, Zevulon military industries base and Krayot using drones and rockets.[534] The IDF said that a factory near Nahariya was struck.[535]
  • The Al-Quds Brigades announced the death of two of its fighters from the Tulkarm Brigade while confronting Israeli forces in the Nur Shams refugee camp.[536]
  • Wafa reported that Israeli soldiers forced Palestinian farmers to leave their lands in Khirbet Yanun in Aqraba, Nablus after seizing their equipment while they were picking olives.[537]
  • Hezbollah claimed that it attacked Israeli forces east of Maroun al-Ras and in Safed using rockets.[538]
  • Six people, including four children were reportedly wounded in Sheikh Radwan clinic, a clinic hosting the polio vaccination campaign in northern Gaza. The IDF denied responsibility for the attack.[539][540]
  • An IDF soldier was killed in a grenade explosion in northern Gaza, which was apparently not related directly to the fighting.[541][542][543]
  • Two other soldiers, both of them of the Givati Brigade's Shaked battalion, were killed in northern Gaza. They were killed by an IED explosion whilst searching a building, increasing the IDF death toll in Gaza to 371.[542][543]
  • The IDF said that it killed Jaafar Khader Faour, a commander of the Nasser Brigade rocket unit of Hezbollah in southern Lebanon who was responsible for several attacks on Israel since October 2023.[544]
  • Hezbollah launched about 100 rockets from Lebanon towards Israel.[545]
  • Al-Quds Brigades said that its rockets targeted Sderot, Mefalsim and other communities near Gaza.[546]
  • A suspected quadcopter strike on the personal vehicle of a female UNICEF staff member working on the polio vaccination campaign while travelling through Jabalia–Nazla damaged the car. But the staff member was not wounded.[547]
  • An Israeli airstrike in Hazmieh killed a Bangladeshi expatriate worker when he entered a coffee shop on his way to work.[548]
  • More than 50 children were reportedly killed in Israeli strikes in Jabalia in the past two days.[547]
  • An Israeli artillery strike in Bureij refugee camp killed a man who worked as a driver for delivering humanitarian aid.[549]

3 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 27 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,341.[550][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 18 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon a day prior.[551]
  • A drone was launched from the "east" towards the Golan Heights.[552]
  • The IDF said that it killed two key Hezbollah militants one responsible of missile launching plans towards communities in the Galilee panhandle, particularly Metula, and another who issued anti-tank fire at Israeli communities and forces in the Galilee. The IDF also said that it killed a PIJ militant in Gaza who served as assistant to the head of the Nukhaba of the Khan Yunis Brigade and raided Nir Oz on October 7.[553]
  • Wafa reported that an Israeli airstrike on a house in Jabalia killed three civilians and injured others.[554]
  • Israeli forces temporarily closed an access road using barbed wire in the Old City of Hebron, blocking students from reaching Ziad Jaber Elementary School for facilitating the passage of Israeli settlers to the Ibrahimi Mosque.[555]
  • Wafa reported that an Israeli air strike in al-Jarn neighbourhood of Jabalia killed a woman and her daughter.[556]
  • An Israeli drone strike in the Khirbet al-Adas area, northeast of Rafah killed a woman and her two children.[556]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents of a building in Duris and its surroundings to move no less than 500 meters.[557] Later, at least three strikes were reported in the area.[558]
  • The IDF arrested 16 people including a child from the West Bank.[559]
  • The IDF said that it killed 900 militants since the start of the Second battle of Jabalia and detained 700 Palestinians, among whom at least 300 were confirmed as members of militant groups. It also said that it located and destroyed a large underground Hamas weapons manufacturing plant in the vicinity of Zeitoun neighborhood of Gaza City.[543]
  • Israeli settlers, accompanied by Israeli forces stole olive harvests belonging to local Palestinian farmers in Al-Mughayyir, Ramallah.[560]
  • An Israeli air strike on a residential house in Khan Yunis killed seven people, including four children.[561]
  • A man died of injuries sustained in a rocket attack in Nahariya on 23 October.[562]
  • Hezbollah claimed to have inflicted casualties and injuries among the crew of a Merkava tank in Metula by firing a guided missile.[563]
  • Israeli forces killed a 14-year-old Palestinian child in Halhoul.[564]
  • Gaza Civil Defence spokesman said that over 100,000 people are suffering from food, water and medicine shortages in north Gaza.[565]
  • An Israeli strike on a health centre in Bazouriyeh killed two paramedics and injured several others.[566]
  • Israeli forces struck the children's floor, the nursery department, and the water tanks of Kamal Adwan Hospital. It also shelled the hospital during a WHO delegation visit. A child was seriously injured.[567][568]
  • The IDF announced that it conducted a ground raid in Syria and seized a Syrian citizen whom it accused of spying for Iran.[569]
  • An Israeli strike in the vicinity of Burj el-Shemali camp hit UNRWA's premises.[570]
  • Hezbollah launched approximately 100 rockets towards Israel.[571]
  • The IDF announced that it captured Ali Soleiman al-Assi, an alleged spy for Iran who gathered intelligence on Israeli troops in the Golan Heights, during a raid by the Egoz Unit on his home near Quneitra several months ago.[572]

4 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 33 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,374.[573][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 16 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon a day prior.[574]
  • Wafa reported that Israeli soldiers ransacked several houses during a raid in Beit Ummar.[575]
  • Israeli strikes damaged the Governmental Hospitals in Tebnine and Baalbek and injured at least 10 people.[576]
  • Israeli settlers burned approximately 20 vehicles belonging to Palestinians in El-Bireh and attacked Burqa.[577][578]
  • Israeli forces killed four people and injuring three others in a bombing in the Lebanese town of Machghara.[579]
  • Israeli forces strike in central Nuseirat killed one person and injured two more.[580]
  • The IDF said that IAF jets killed Abu Ali Rida, Hezbollah commander in Baraachit who was also responsible for planning and conducting rocket and anti-tank missile attacks on Israeli soldiers.[581]
  • Drone were launched from the "east" towards the Golan Heights and Israel.[582]
  • The Gaza Government Media Office said that all hospitals in northern Gaza are out of service.[583]
  • An Israeli air strike in Nuseirat refugee camp wounded five people, including children.[584]
  • The IDF arrested at least 12 people including a teenager and a media activist from the West Bank.[585]
  • Wafa reported that Israeli settlers attacked Palestinian olive pickers using sticks and stones in Berin, while the IDF prevented two families from reaching their land.[586]
  • An Israeli airstrike in central Gaza wounded two Palestinian olive pickers and killed five others.[587]
  • SANA reported an Israeli strike in the vicinity of Sayyidah Zaynab. The IAF said that its jets carried out strikes targeting targets of Hezbollah intelligence headquarters in Syria.[588][589]
  • Israeli shelling hit Kamal Adwan Hospital, injuring patients including children and some medical staff.[590]
  • The al-Qassam Brigades said that it targeted Israeli forces east of the Shujayea neighbourhood of Gaza City using mortar rounds and al-Quds Brigades said that it detonated an explosive device in an IDF vehicle east of Jabalia refugee camp.[591]
  • A Gaza civil defence spokesperson said that over 1,300 people were killed since the start of the Siege of North Gaza.[592]
