  • The al-Qassam Brigades claimed that it killed and injured four Israeli soldiers who took refugee inside a home in al-Qassasib neighborhood of the Jabalia refugee camp and targeted a Merkava tank in the same area.[593]
  • Israeli settlers attacked and injured two female IDF soldiers in the illegal outpost of Giv'at Asaf in the West Bank.[594]
  • The US Army announced that a soldier who sustained critical injuries during a non-combat incident in May while supporting the Gaza floating pier died from his wounds on 31 October.[595][596]
  • An Israeli air strike on a home in Beit Lahia killed at least 25 people including 13 children and trapped several people under the rubble.[597]
  • Israeli defense minister Yoav Gallant approved the IDF's recommendation for issuing a second round of 7,000 orders to haredim for serving in the IDF.[598]

5 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 17 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,391.[599][a]
  • Israeli prime minister Benjamin Netanyahu fired Defence minister Yoav Gallant from his position for disagreements with post-war plans for Gaza and replaced him with Israel Katz.[600]
  • An Israeli strike on tents in Deir el-Balah killed two people, including a child.[601]
  • An Israeli strike on a tent in the Maen area east of Khan Yunis killed three people including a child.[602]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it launched three drone strikes on a "vital target" in Haifa.[603]
  • The IDF announced that a soldier of the 932nd Battalion in Nahal Brigade was critically wounded during combat in southern Lebanon a day prior.[604]
  • The IDF announced that it killed two Hezbollah militants with dual Asian nationalities who infiltrated Israel during the conflict.[605]
  • An Israeli strike on tents in the az-Zawayda killed six people, including a six-year-old child and a four-year-old child.[606]
  • The NNA reported that the IDF destroyed over 37 towns with approximately 40,000 housing units in southern Lebanon, centred in the area from Naqoura to the outskirts of Khiam. The IDF said that it targeted Hezbollah infrastructure.[607][608]
  • The IDF and Shin Bet claimed to have arrested over 60 PFLP members from the West Bank and Lebanon.[609]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it launched six drones on Israel.[610]
  • The IDF withdrew several brigades from southern Lebanon.[611]
  • Kamal Adwan Hospital was attacked by Israeli quadcopters.[612]
  • SANA reported an Israeli strike on an industrial zone in Al-Qusayr, Syria.[613] The IDF said that it struck a facility belonging to Hezbollah's munition unit.[614]
  • Two elderly Palestinian patients, including a cancer patient died while waiting to cross an Israeli checkpoint in the vicinity of the Indonesian Hospital while fleeing from Beit Lahia.[615][616]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 11 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon a day prior.[617]
  • Israeli soldiers detained a Birzeit University student and a female psychiatrist working for the Palestine Red Crescent Society from the West Bank.[618]
  • An Israeli strike on a residential building in Barja killed at least 30 people and injured several others including a woman and her child.[619]

6 November

  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 37 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon.[620]
  • Israeli forces shot and killed two men accused of attempting a ramming attack targeting Israeli forces in Qabatiya.[621]
  • An Israeli strike on a house in Block C of the Nuseirat refugee camp injured eight people including two women and five children.[622]
  • Clashes were reported between the IDF and the Jenin Battalion in Jenin.[623]
  • Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it launched a drone strike towards a site in southern Israel and another strike towards a "vital target" in Haifa.[624]
  • An Israeli drone strike on another home in Nuseirat refugee camp wounded at least six people, including two women and three children.[625]
  • An Israeli strike on a home in Beit Lahia killed the wife of a Palestinian prisoner and her three children.[626]
  • An Israeli strike on a building serving as shelter for displaced people in the al-Manshiyya area of Beit Lahia killed at least 15 people.[627]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents in some areas of Nabatieh and Bourj el-Barajneh to move at least 500 metres.[628][629]
  • Hezbollah claimed to have wounded the crew of a Merkava tank in Metula by targeting it using a guided missile and killed and injured Israeli soldiers by striking a home in the same area.[630]
  • An Israeli soldier was killed when Hezbollah fired rockets on Avivim, a locality in Israel next to the Lebanon border. Three other soldiers were lightly injured.[631]
  • The IDF detained at least 12 Palestinians including a woman from the West Bank.[632]
  • A driver accused of crashing his car into a bus stop in Shilo and slightly injuring two civilians was shot and killed.[633]
  • An IDF dog attacked a three-year-old Palestinian child during a raid in Qabatiya.[634]
  • Over 150 rockets were launched by Hezbollah from Lebanon towards Israel, with one striking the area of Ben Gurion Airport and debris damaging a car in Ra'anana.[635] Sharpnel from a Hezbollah rocket barrage in Kfar Masaryk killed a 18-year-old man.[636][637]
  • The IDF withdrew its 252nd Division from Gaza.[638]
  • A projectile was launched from central Gaza towards southern Israel.[639]
  • An Israeli air strike on a house north of the Nuseirat refugee camp killed at least four people including a child and injured 17 others.[640]
  • WHO chief Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus said that up to 10,000 children could not be reached for receiving a second dose and added that "efforts will continue to reach more children through regular health services".[641]

7 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 78 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 48 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,469.[642][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 53 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon in the past 24 hours.[643]
  • Israeli police said that it shot and "neutralised" a suspect accused of trying to conduct a ramming attack against police officers in 'Anata.[644]
  • The Knesset passed laws allowing deportation of family members of "terrorists"[645] and allowing the firing of teachers showing sympathy towards "terrorism".[646][647]
  • Hezbollah announced that an Israeli strike in Bazouriyeh killed an uncle of Hassan Nasrallah alongside his family.[648]
  • Palestinian fighters targeted Israeli forces using an explosive device during clashes in Tulkarm.[649]
  • The IDF said that it conducted over 110 strikes on targets in Lebanon and Gaza one day prior. It also said that fighter jets struck about 20 sites in the Bekaa Valley and north of the Litani River, killing approximately 60 Hezbollah operatives and dozens of sites in other parts of Lebanon. Israeli ground forces also destroyed militant infrastructure including a "rocket launcher used for an attack in central Israel and weapon depots. The IDF said that it killed an estimated 50 militants in Jabalia and Beit Lahia and killed a number of militants in Rafah. It also said that its 91st and 36th divisions demolished a Hezbollah military warehouse and a rocket launcher.[650][651]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it launched a drone towards an IDF target in "territories occupied by Israel".[652]
  • Israeli brigadier general Itzik Cohen said that the IDF will not allow northern Gaza residents to return to their houses and also said that humanitarian aid will not be regularly allowed to northern Gaza for preventing regrouping of Hamas militants, adding that there are "no more civilians left" in north Gaza.[653]
  • The IDF arrested at least 18 Palestinians including two girls from the West Bank.[654]
  • Israeli strike in various areas of Rafah killed six people, including three children.[655][656]
  • An Israeli airstrike on a car at a checkpoint in Sidon killed three people and injured three Lebanese soldiers and six Malaysian peacekeepers.[657][658]
  • An Israeli strike on a school serving as shelter for displaced people in the Al-Shati refugee camp killed 12 people including women and children.[659][660]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for an area northwest of Gaza City, saying that Palestinian militants launched rockets from there.[661]
  • Hezbollah claimed to have killed and wounded an Israeli infantry force which attempted to advance towards Yaroun.[662]
  • An Israeli air strike on a house in Jabalia refugee camp killed 27 people.[663]
  • Israeli settlers attacked a Palestinian home, physical attacked the family and set a vehicle on fire in Jaba', Jenin.[664]
  • A Palestinian woman was injured on her face after Israeli soldiers fired a tear gas canister at her car during a raid in Al-Khader.[665]

8 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 39 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,508.[666][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 15 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon a day prior.[667]
  • An Israeli air strike on a home in the Daraj neighbourhood of Gaza City killed at least nine people including children and women.[668]
  • The Houthis claimed that its air defences downed an American General Atomics MQ-9 Reaper in al Jawf Governorate.[669]
  • Palestinian fighters targeted Israeli forces using an explosive device in Balata refugee camp.[670]
  • The IDF said that a soldier who fired grenades at already heavily bombed buildings in Gaza for celebrating the victory of Donald Trump in the 2024 United States presidential election would be "disciplined" by his commanders.[671]
  • A fisherman was killed and three others were injured during attacks by Israeli forces on the coast of Rafah.[672]
  • Israeli forces entered the French-administered Church of the Pater Noster on the Mount of Olives in occupied East Jerusalem and briefly detained two French consulate gendarmes with diplomatic status.[673]
  • Israeli forces shot and "neutralized" a motorist in the Shu'fat refugee camp, north of occupied East Jerusalem.[674]
  • The Israeli foreign ministry said that 10 Israelis were wounded following clashes between pro-Palestinian protesters and Maccabi Tel Aviv F.C fans before and after a Europa League football match between AFC Ajax and Maccabi Tel Aviv F.C in Amsterdam. Violence broke out after Maccabi Tel Aviv F.C fans started climbing the walls of private buildings and tearing down Palestinian flags hanging from their windows. Dutch authorities called the incidents "antisemitic".[675][676]
  • Hezbollah claimed to have hit Israeli forces in Jal al-Hammar, south of Odaisseh.[677]
  • An Israeli soldier in the Alon Brigade died of injuries sustained in an October 26 clash with Hezbollah fighters in southern Lebanon, in which five other Israeli soldiers were reported killed earlier.[678]
  • An Israeli air strike on a medical center in Tyre district on the road connecting Deir Qanoun to Ras al-Ain and Naqoura killed a paramedic from Tayr Harfa.[679]
  • Wafa reported that civilians were wounded by Israeli shelling of the Halima Al-Sadia School in Jabalia refugee camp.[680]
  • The NNA reported that the IDF detonated explosives planted inside homes in Yaroun, Aitaroun and Maroun al-Ras "with the aim of destroying residential homes there".[681]
  • Al Jazeera reported that Israeli strikes in Beit Lahia struck residential houses and agricultural land and trapped people including civilians under the rubble.[682]
  • A missile was launched from Yemen towards Israel.[683] The Houthis said that it targeted Nevatim Airbase using a Palestine 2 hypersonic ballistic rocket.[669]
  • Israeli settlers attacked Palestinian olive-pickers in Deir Jarir and cut down approximately 70 olive, grape, and almond trees belonging to Palestinian residents in Nahalin.[684]
  • Hezbollah claimed to have hit Israeli soldiers using missiles in Margaliot and Misgav Am.[685]
  • The Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights said that it verified the identities of 8,119 people died from the war, of which almost 70% were women and children. The IDF said that the civilian-militant ratio was 1:1 which it blamed on Hamas and its use of civilian facilities. Hamas denied the claim.[686] Israeli diplomatic mission in Geneva said that it "categorically rejects" the "damning" UN report on its conduct during its Gaza war and accused that UN relied on "unverified information".[687]
  • A man was injured after falling from a ladder due to rocket sirens in the Lower Galilee.[688]
  • The Qassam Brigades said that it attacked Israeli soldiers using mortar rounds southeast of Shujayea, Gaza City. PIJ said that it targeted a group of Israeli soldiers using mortar fire along the Netzarim Corridor.[689]
  • An Israeli drone strike on a home in Abasan al-Jadida, Khan Yunis Governorate killed a Palestinian child.[690]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents of an area in Dahieh to move at least 500 metres. Later, at least 14 Israeli air strikes was conducted on the outskirts of Beirut. The IDF said that it struck Hezbollah command headquarters, a weapons production site, and other infrastructure.[691][692]
  • An Israeli airstrike in Aleppo and Idlib injured several Syrian soldiers.[693]
  • The IDF said that it stepped up humanitarian efforts including opening an additional crossing.[694]

9 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 44 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,552.[695][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 19 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon a day prior.[696]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said it launched a drone towards an IDF target in northern Israel.[697]
  • Israeli forces detained and assaulted several Palestinians during a raid in the Ras area in the vicinity of Wadi al-Hussein, east of Hebron.[698]
  • The Jenin Brigades claimed to have hit IDF vehicles by detonating a "highly explosive device" in Silat ad-Dhahr.[699]
  • Israeli fighter jets struck two buildings in Tyre killing at least nine people, including a pregnant woman and a child and injured 38 others.[700]
  • The IDF said that its 162nd Division killed dozens of militants and destroyed a weapons warehouse in Jabalia in the past day. It also said that the Nahal Brigade killed militants, located weapons and destroyed militant infrastructure in Rafah. It added that the IAF struck over 50 militant targets in Lebanon and the Gaza Strip in the past 24 hours.[701]
  • An Israeli air strike on Fahd al-Sabah school serving as shelter for displaced Palestinians in the Tuffah neighborhood of Gaza City killed at least six people from two families including two journalists.[702][703]
  • An Israeli strike on tents in Israeli-designated safe zone in the al-Mawasi area of Khan Yunis killed at least nine Palestinians including women and children and injured several others.[704][705]
  • Clashes erupted inside 'Aqqaba after the IDF sent a number of vehicles, accompanied by a bulldozer, from the Hamra and Tayasir checkpoints to surround several houses and arrest a number of Palestinians, killing one person.[706] The IDF announced that it killed a Palestinian gunman in an exchange of fire and arrested five Palestinians from Tubas and 'Aqqaba. It said that it located weapons and money during its operation in Tubas.[707]
  • Hezbollah claimed that its air defence unit shot down an Israeli Elbit Hermes 450 drone using a surface-to-air missile in Lebanese territory.[708]
  • Israeli strikes in southern Lebanon killed 11 people including 6 rescuers affiliated to the Amal Movement and Hezbollah.[709]
  • The al-Qassam Brigades said that it targeted an IDF bulldozer using an RPG shell in the al-Qassasib neighbourhood of Jabalia.[710]
  • Wafa reported that Israeli Navy killed three Palestinian men by targeting them using gunfire from warships as they were in the vicinity of al-Khalidi Mosque along the coastal road northwest of Gaza City soon after releasing them from detention after detaining them during IDF's offensive in northern Gaza in early October.[711]
  • Qatar said Hamas-Israel negotiations are on hold. Ten days earlier Qatar said it would suspend mediation efforts if no agreement was made in that round of negotiations, and indeed no agreement was made in that round. Qatar said it is not withdrawing from mediation and negotiations will resume when the parties show "seriousness" to end the war. Hamas said that it accepted the three-phase Israel–Hamas war ceasefire proposal and rejected a new short-term ceasefire proposal. Earlier, there were media reports, citing anonymous sources in U.S. administration, that portrayed Qatar's decision as Qatar expelling Hamas from the country at U.S. behest. These reports were explicitly denied by Qatar. Qatar said reports of closing Hamas' bureau in Qatar are inaccurate and the bureau was, and is, an important channel of communication. Qatar noted how, during negotiations, there was "manipulation" by using negotiations as an excuse for prolonging the war, and by reneging on previously agreed-upon commitments.[712][713][714][715][excessive citations]
  • Israeli air strikes in the southern suburbs of Beirut extensively damaged some buildings of the Rafik Hariri University in Hadath, Mount Lebanon.[716]
  • Locals told Wafa that Israeli forces fired toxic tear gas canisters at residents and their houses, resulting in several people suffering from suffocation during an IDF raid in Abu Dis.[717]

10 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 51 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,603.[718][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 53 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon a day prior.[719]
  • An Israeli air strike in Tyre killed a woman and her four disabled siblings.[720]
  • Israeli missile strikes on tents serving as shelter for displaced Palestinians on the grounds of Al-Aqsa Hospital killed two Palestinians and injured 26 others including journalists.[721][722]
  • The Houthi-affiliated Al-Masirah reported that US and UK forces launched air strikes on Sanaa, 'Amran Governorate and other areas of Yemen. US officials confirmed the strikes, saying that US forces conducted multiple air strikes on facilities used by Houthis for storing weapons.[723][724]
  • IDF spokesperson Avichay Adraee said that burning of Flag of Lebanon by some soldiers was a violation of its orders.[725]
  • An Israeli strike destroyed a home in Old Gaza Street of northern Jabalia refugee camp killing at least 36 Palestinians including 13 children and nine women and wounded several others and several others went missing. The IDF said that it targeted a site where militants operated, without offering evidence.[726][727][728][729]
  • An Israeli strike on the civil defense centre affiliated to the Islamic Mission Scouts Association in Ras al-Ain, Lebanon killed 15 people and injured two others.[730][731]
  • An Israeli strike on a home in Ain Baal injured five people including civilians.[730]
  • An Israeli strike in Srifa caused critical to moderate injuries to several people including civilians and severely damaged a hospital's equipment.[730]
  • Israeli settlers cut down various types of trees owned by a Palestinian resident in the outskirts of Nahalin.[732]
  • An Israeli strike on a home in Almat, Jbeil district killed 23 people including seven children and wounded six others.[733]
  • An Israeli strike on a civil defence center affiliated with the Islamic Health Authority in Adloun killed three paramedics.[734]
  • The US suspended the delivery of 130 D9 bulldozers to Israel.[735]
  • SANA reported that an Israeli air strike in Sayyidah Zaynab inflicted casualties. The Syrian Observatory for Human Rights reported that nine people—including a woman, three children, and a Hezbollah commander were killed and 14 others were injured in an apartment.[736][737] The Syrian Ministry of Defense reported that the strikes killed seven civilians including women and children and wounded 20 others.[738]
  • Civil defence authorities eased restrictions in northern Israel excluding area closest to the Lebanese border.[739]
  • An Israeli strike on a house in Gaza City killed Wael al-Khour, a minister in the Hamas-run government, his wife and three children.[727]
  • Israeli prime minister Benjamin Netanyahu reportedly acknowledged for the first time that Israel was behind the pager and walkie-talkie attacks during a cabinet meeting. He stated that the operations "were carried out despite the opposition of senior officials in the defense establishment and those responsible for them in the political echelon".[740]
  • A Hezbollah anti-tank missile attack injured three people in Metula, while a separate rocket attack in Kabri injured three others.[741]
  • Hezbollah claimed to have hit Haifa naval base using drones.[742]
  • Two drones were launched from "the east" towards Israel.[743] The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it conducted drone strikes on "vital targets" in the northern and southern Israel.[744]
  • The al-Qassam Brigades claimed to have killed 15 Israeli soldiers from close range using an antitank rocket, grenades and light weapons in Beit Lahia.[745]
  • IDF Chief of Staff Herzi Halevi approved an expansion of its ground operation in southern Lebanon.[746]

11 November

  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 54 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon a day prior.[747]
  • A projectile was launched from Yemen towards Israel.[748]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq also said that it launched five drone strikes towards IDF targets in northern and southern Israel.[749]
  • In the Nuseirat camp, three people were killed and multiple people were injured after Israeli forces attacked tents housing displaced people. In a separate attack an Israeli quadcopter struck a group of people installing a water pipe network, killing two people.[750] An Israeli strike on a tent killed a journalist and his wife.[751]
  • Al-Masirah reported that US and UK forces conducted multiple air attacks in 'Amran Governorate and Saada Governorate.[752]
  • Israeli gunfire during clashes in the Jalazone refugee camp wounded five Palestinians including a child.[753]
  • The Houthis said that it launched a hypersonic ballistic missile towards an IDF base near Tel Aviv.[754]
  • Hezbollah spokesman Mohammad Afif stated that Israel has not managed to capture "a single" village in Lebanon so far during the invasion, he also dismissed the IDF claim of a significant decline of Hezbollah's missile stockpile as "just lies".[755]
  • SANA reported an Israeli airstrike in the vicinity of Shinshar.[756]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents of 21 towns in southern Lebanon to move to north of the Awali River.[757]
  • Hezbollah launched 165 projectiles at northern Israel. Fifty rockets targeted the Karmiel area, wounding three people including a child in Bi'ina.[758] Another 90 rockets were fired at Haifa Bay, damaging houses and vehicles in Kiryat Ata and injuring four people.[759]
  • The al-Qassam Brigades said that it targeted a Merkava 4 tank using rockets in the Saftawi area, west of the Jabalia refugee camp.[760]
  • Satellite photos analyzed by The Associated Press showed that the IDF started construction of a road along the so-called Alpha Line which separates the Israeli-occupied Golan Heights from Syria, while Israeli soldiers entered this demilitarized zone during the construction, violating cease-fire rules governing the area.[761]
  • An Israeli airstrike on a building in Ain Yaaqoub killed at least 14 people, injured 15 others and trapped some people under the rubble.[762]
  • Israel said that it implemented the majority of US demands on aid for Gaza.[763]
  • The US Central Command said that it struck nine targets in two places that it claimed were affiliated with Iranian-backed groups as a response to several attacks on US personnel in Syria in the past 24 hours.[764]
  • An Israeli drone strike on a small cafe in the Israeli-designated humanitarian zone in al-Mawasi, Khan Yunis killed 11 people including five minors and injured dozens.[765][766]
  • A car-ramming attack in the vicinity of al-Khader wounded two Israelis.[767]
  • Israeli air strikes killed at least 20 Palestinians in Nuseirat refugee camp.[768]

12 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 62 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 48 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,665.[769][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 44 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon a day prior.[770]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it launched drones towards an IDF target in the "south of the occupied territories".[771]
  • The IDF announced that four soldiers of the 900th Brigade were killed while fighting in Beit Lahia, bringing the IDF death toll in Gaza to 375.[772][773]
  • The IDF called on the residents in areas of Haret Hreik, Ghobeiry, Lailaki and Hadath to evacuate.[774] Later, at least 13 Israeli air strikes hit the southern suburbs of Beirut.[775]
  • The IDF said that COGAT, in cooperation with international aid organisations delivered hundreds of food and water packages to Jabalia and Beit Hanoun. It claimed that 741 aid trucks were delivered since October to northern Gaza through the Erez Crossing.[776] International aid organizations in a joint statement accused Israel of failing to meet the US demands for allowing more humanitarian aid for Gaza and said that conditions are worse than at any point since the start of war.[777]
  • The NNA reported that the outskirts of Yater and Zibqin were subjected to artillery shelling using incendiary phosphorous shells.[778]
  • Al-Masirah reported that the United States and the United Kingdom launched air strikes targeting a civilian car in As Sawma'ah District and the Al Faza area in at-Tuhayta district.[779]
  • Hezbollah claimed that its air defense unit forced an Israeli Elbit Hermes 450 drone to leave Lebanese airspace by confronting it above Nabatieh Governorate.[780]
  • The IDF said that it opened the Kissufim Crossing in the vicinity of Khan Yunis for facilitating food, water, medical supplies, and shelter equipment delivery to central and southern Gaza.[781]
  • The IDF told residents to evacuate from 14 villages in southern Lebanon to the north of the Awali River.[782]
  • A Hezbollah drone struck a kindergarten in Nesher, causing slight damage.[783]
  • An Israeli strike on a group of Palestinians waiting for aid killed 12 people and injured several others.[784]
  • An Israeli air strike on an overcrowded area in the vicinity of al-Noor Mosque in the western part of Deir el-Balah killed at least six people including two infants.[785]
  • The IDF called on people in an evacuation centre and a school sheltering hundreds of Palestinians in Beit Hanoun to flee southwards.[786]
  • Israeli forces shot dead a Palestinian man in a checkpoint in the vicinity of Deir Sharaf. The IDF said that the man was armed with a knife and tried to stab soldiers in the checkpoint.[787]
  • Hezbollah fired a barrage of ten rockets at the Western Galilee, killing two men in Nahariya and injuring two others in Kabri.[788]
  • The Houthis said that it targeted a US aircraft carrier in the Arabian Sea using cruise missiles and drones and targeted two American destroyers in the Red Sea with ballistic missiles and drones. The Pentagon confirmed a Houthi attack on two American destroyers while transiting the Bab-el-Mandeb and said that its warships shot down drones and missiles launched by them, adding that it was unaware of any attack against a US aircraft carrier.[789][790]
  • An Israeli drone strike on a tent in Deir el-Balah killed two people and injured several people including children.[791]
  • An Israeli air strike in Joun killed 15 people including eight women and four children and wounded 12 others.[792]

13 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 47 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,712.[793][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 78 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon a day prior.[794]
  • The US Central Command said that it conducted strikes against a weapons storage and logistics headquarters facility of an Iranian-backed group after an attack on American personnel one day prior.[795]
  • The NNA reported that Israeli fighter jets conducted a series of strikes in the southern suburbs of Beirut, hitting Dar al-Hawra Medical Centre in Harek Hreik several times after issuing evacuation orders for the area[796] and in Ghobeiry.[797] The IDF said that it struck weapons depots and command headquarters of Hezbollah.[798]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it launched two drone strikes on Israel.[799][800]
  • Israeli settlers burned a number of vehicles owned by Palestinians in the East Jerusalem neighbourhood of Sheikh Jarrah.[801]
  • Israel Hayom reported that senior IDF officers said that there is "procrastination" for presenting a probe of the October 7 attack. It also reported that the IDF justifies the delay by pointing to the tense operational situations in the north in the last few months.[802]
  • A nine-year-old girl died from serious injuries sustained in an Israeli strike on a tent two days prior which killed her parents. Her brother was also seriously wounded.[803]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for areas of Bourj al-Barajneh and Dahieh. Later, Israeli air strikes hit the areas.[804][805][806]
  • An employee was charged by the US government for the alleged leak of classified documents on Israel's preparation for attacking Iran.[807][808][809]
  • Israeli air strikes on a house and in the Israeli-designed safe zone in al-Mawasi killed at least eight Palestinians and trapped several others under the rubble.[810]
  • An Israeli air strike on a home in the Jabalia refugee camp killed at least 10 Palestinians including children.[811]
  • Hezbollah claimed that its drones hit Kirya IDF base in Tel Aviv, saying that it was the headquarters of the Israeli war cabinet and general staff, as well as a war management room and the IAF's war control and supervision authority.[812]
  • Haaretz reported that the IDF was preparing to stay in Gaza until at least the end of 2025.[813]
  • Wafa reported clashes between locals and the IDF in Beit Ummar after the latter demolished several Palestinian structures, including two houses. It also reported that Israeli settlers seeking to takeover areas surrounding Ras Ain al-Auja cleared the land and destroyed properties.[814]
  • The IDF detained Esra Ghorani, a female reporter of Wafa and a crew of the Palestinian Broadcasting Corporation crew in an IDF checkpoint in Tayasir after they covered the demolition of a home by the IDF in Kardala.[815]
  • SANA reported that Israeli strikes targeted Al-Qusayr and said that Syrian air defences intercepted "hostile" targets above the Homs countryside and the strikes caused "significant damage". Israel said that it was conducting strikes to decrease the transfer of weapons from Iran via Syria to Hezbollah in Lebanon, which it said had spread to Al-Qusayr.[816][817]
  • Six Israeli soldiers from the Golani Brigade's 51st Battalion were killed and one was injured during a shootout with four Hezbollah fighters in southern Lebanon, who were also killed.[818]
  • An IDF raid on a home in Ezbet al-Jarad, east of Tulkarm killed people and injured two others including a two-year-old child.[819]
  • The US Central Command said that it hit multiple Houthi weapons storage facilities in Yemen on 9 November and 10 November.[820]
  • An Israeli strike hit a tent serving as shelter for orphans and street vendors, killing two people.[821]
  • An Israeli strike on a house in northern Gaza killed three siblings aged below six.[822]
  • European Union foreign policy chief Josep Borrell proposed suspending political dialogue with Israel due to the war in Gaza.[823]
  • An Israeli strike in Joun killed Sakina Mansour Kawtharani, a radio journalist of al-Nour, her two children and other members of the family.[824]
  • An Israeli air strike on a tent in Israeli-designated safe zone in al-Mawasi, Khan Yunis wounded several people and damaged Médecins Sans Frontières's clinic.[825][826]

14 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 24 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,736.[827][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 16 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon a day prior.[828]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it launched drone strikes on a "vital target" in northern Israel.[829]
  • Haaretz reported that the IDF will investigate whether at least 16 strikes in northern Gaza violated international law.[830]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for areas of Haret Hreik, Bourj al-Barajneh, Chouaifet and Ghobeiry highlighting some buildings saying that they are Hezbollah infrastructure. Later, an Israeli drone strike hit in the vicinity of Rawadat al-Shahedain in Ghobeiry and an Israeli missile strike hit Choueifat.[831][832][833][834][835] The IDF said that its air strikes targeted weapons storage of Hezbollah.[836]
  • A one-year-old boy died in the Al-Aqsa Martyrs Hospital due to lack of medical supplies after a WHO request to allow him to leave the Gaza Strip was rejected by the IDF.[837]
  • The IDF claimed to have killed 200 Hezbollah militants and destroyed over 140 Hezbollah rocket launchers in the last week. It said that its strikes on offensive capabilities of Hezbollah on 13 November and 12 November killed the operations head of a Hezbollah battalion, the head of a battalion anti-aircraft unit of Hezbollah and a company commander in the Redwan force.[838]
  • The UN Special Committee to investigate Israeli practices found that the IDF's war methods in Gaza is consistent with genocide. Israel denied the claim.[839][840]
  • An Israeli drone strike on a group of people taking a delivery of commercial trucks in Maghazi refugee camp killed five people.[841]
  • Hezbollah claimed to have inflicted casualties on Israeli soldiers in the eastern outskirts of Markaba with a missile.[842]
  • The IDF said that it struck over 30 Hezbollah sites in Dahieh over the past two days, including command centers and weapon depots.[843]
  • Gaza Civil Defence said that "around 30 people, all civilians" were injured in the Israeli strikes in Gaza City, Jabalia and Rafah.[827]
  • The NNA reported that Israeli soldiers and Hezbollah fighters were engaged in violent clashes in the outskirts of Aitaroun towards Ainata and said that there were confirmed casualties among the Israeli soldiers.[844]
  • Israeli bombardment of Al-Hebbariyah killed a farmer.[844]
  • An Israeli strike on a residential building in Mazzeh and another Israeli strike on a residential building in Qudsaya killed 23 people including seven civilians. Israeli Army Radio said that the strikes targeted assets and headquarters of PIJ.[845][846][847] PIJ confirmed the death of two of its leaders and a group of its caders.[848]
  • Israeli shelling in Jabalia killed at least 10 Palestinians, mostly women and children.[849]
  • An Israeli drone strike on a tent sheltering displaced people in Bureij refugee camp killed at least four Palestinians including children.[850]
  • Two Palestinian children were injured by Israeli gunfire in Beit Furik.[851]
  • An Israeli platoon commander of the Golani Brigade's 51st Battalion was killed and two other soldiers were wounded during a shootout in southern Lebanon.[852]
  • Two Israeli soldiers were moderately injured in a Hezbollah drone attack on Eliakim.[853]
  • At least two unknown gunmen fired around 30 shots toward a UNIFIL patrol near Qalaouiyah after it discovered an ammunition cache, causing no casualties.[854][855]
  • A Human Rights Watch report said that the IDF's forced displacement of hundreds of thousands of Palestinians amounts to crimes against humanity.[856] The IDF accused Human Rights Watch of "blatant misrepresentations" and "factual distortion".[857]
  • An Israeli strike in Arabsalim killed six people, including five paramedics.[846][858]
  • Haaretz reported that Israeli police suspect that Netanyahu's chief of staff, Tzachi Braverman, attempted to manipulate the timelines of the former's conversation on October 7 surrounding the October 7 attacks to his military secretary Avi Gil to make it favourable for Netanyahu.[859]
  • An Israeli airstrike on a civil defense center in Duris, Lebanon killed at least 15 people. A separate strike in the city killed eight, including five women, and injured 27.[860][861][862]
  • Israeli forces destroyed a mosque in the Israeli-Arab Bedouin village of Umm al-Hiran in the Negev in a plan approved by the far-right National Security Minister Itamar Ben Gvir.[863]

15 November

  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 59 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon a day prior.[864]
  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 28 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,764.[865][a]
  • An Israeli strike on a residential apartment in the central part of Deir el-Balah killed three people including a woman and her daughter.[866]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents in parts of Ghobeiry and Bourj el-Barajneh. Later, Israeli air raids were reported in the area.[867][868][869] The IDF said that it struck targets including Hezbollah command centers. It also claimed to have struck and destroyed a rockets stockpile and 15 launchers in southern Lebanon used for firing projectiles towards central Israel two day prior.[870]
  • The IDF claimed to have hit a Hezbollah command centre in Nabatieh Governorate. It said that the IAF hit over 120 Hezbollah targets throughout Lebanon in the past day, including weapons storage facilities, command centres and a large number of rocket launchers used for striking northern Israel.[871]
  • Wafa reported that Israeli soldiers stormed a family house in Qalqilya and assaulted one of its inhabitants. It also reported that soldiers smashed the family's furniture and took gold jewellery.[872]
  • An Israeli artillery strike on a house in Rafah killed two people including a woman.[866]
  • Israeli Army Radio reported that Israeli defense minister Israel Katz decided to approve 7,000 conscription orders for Haredi Jews.[873]
  • A rocket launched from Lebanon to Haifa Bay area hit a construction site, slightly injuring a man. Hezbollah said that it targeted Tira al-Carmel IDF base in southern Haifa.[874][875]
  • A rocket barrage launched from Lebanon towards Haifa area and the Western Galilee injured three male foreign workers.[876]
  • The IDF said that its drone strike killed a group of gunmen in Shejaiya neighborhood of Gaza City including Yasser Ghandhi, who infiltrated into Israel and participated in the October 7 attack.[877]
  • The IDF said that it killed Muhammad Abu Sakhil, the operations chief of PIJ.[878]
  • The IDF claimed that the IAF in coordination with Shin Bet killed Alkaman Abed Elslam Khalil Anbar, the commander of a PIJ brigade situated in Gaza City.[879]
  • The IDF issued evacuation order for residents of some buildings in Haret Hreik, Hadath, Mount Lebanon and those adjacent to it.[880] Later, two Israeli air raids struck Hadath.[881]
  • SANA reported an Israeli strike in Mezzeh.[882]
  • Hezbollah claimed to have inflicted casualties among a group of Israeli soldiers by hitting them using a dive bomber drone.[883]
  • A soldier from the Golani Brigade's 13th Battalion was killed during a shootout with a Hezbollah fighter in a building in southern Lebanon. The latter was also killed during the shootout.[884][885]
  • Two Israeli soldiers were injured in Gaza while seven others were injured in southern Lebanon.[886]
  • The al-Qassam Brigades (Hamas) claimed that it killed three Israeli soldiers at point-blank range near Abbas Kilani roundabout, north of Beit Lahia.[887]
  • Wafa reported that Israeli soldiers damaged belongings in several houses without making arrests in al-Ein refugee camp, western Nablus.[888]
  • Israeli forces killed a Palestinian man who attempted to flee from north Gaza to central Gaza.[889]
  • The family of Al Jazeera cameraman Fadi al-Wahidi who is in a coma after being shot in the neck while reporting the Israeli ground invasion of the Jabalia refugee camp launched a hunger strike to allow his evacuation from Gaza after Israeli authorities rejected appeals from three media freedom organisations.[890]
  • An Israeli air strike destroyed a home in Ain Qana killing five people including a woman and her three children.[891]
  • Wafa reported that Israeli settlers put up a caravan on land belonging to Palestinians in Masafer Yatta while conducting attacks on residents.[892]
  • Israeli authorities demolished the Palestinian al-Bustan Association office in the Silwan neighborhood of East Jerusalem.[893]
  • An artillery shell hit a UNIFIL base in Chamaa without exploding, causing minor damage to its gym.[894][895] Initial reports blamed Israel, however an investigation by the IDF determined that the shell was launched by Hezbollah.[896]

16 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 35 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,799.[897][a]
  • Israeli air strikes on residential buildings near Musab bin Omair Mosque in Beit Lahia caused casualties, including children.[898]
  • Palestinian fighters attacked Israeli forces in Jenin and used an explosive device against Israeli forces in the Old City of Nablus.[899]
  • An Israeli strike in Borj Rahal killed a paramedic and wounded seven others.[900]
  • Al Jazeera reported that the IAF struck a group of Palestinians in Beit Lahia, killing three people including civilians.[901]
  • The IDF issued an evacuation order for residents of two buildings in Haret Hreik.[902] Later, an Israeli strike hit the area. The IDF said that its fighter jets under the direction of the intelligence division hit Hezbollah infrastructure.[903][904]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it launched drones towards "a vital target" in Eilat twice.[905]
  • The Khan Yunis municipality announced that it ran out of fuel.[906]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents in parts of Haret Hreik, Ghobeiry and Burj el-Barajneh. Later, an Israeli air strike hit the southern suburbs of Beirut.[907][908]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents of Tyre, highlighting 14 buildings. Later, a series of Israeli air strikes hit Tyre.[909][910]
  • An Israeli drone struck a civil defence team in Arnoun-Kfar Tebnit road in Nabatieh Governorate killing at least one paramedic, injuring four others and leaving two paramedics missing.[911]
  • Hezbollah claimed that it hit a gathering of Israeli soldiers adjacent to an IDF checkpoint in Avivim with kamikaze drones.[912]
  • An Israeli drone strike on a group of people in Rafah killed seven people including civilians and injured several others.[913]
  • A child died from injuries sustained in an Israeli air strike on a tent housing displaced families in the al-Mawasi area in southern Gaza, an Israeli-designated humanitarian zone.[913]
  • The IDF said that approximately 80 rockets were launched from Lebanon towards Israel.[914] It also said that it struck over 160 militant targets in Lebanon and Gaza in the past day.[915]
  • An Israeli airstrike on Abu Assi School used for housing displaced families in Al-Shati refugee camp killed at least 10 people including women and children and wounded at least 20 others.[916][917]
  • Two rockets were launched from northern Gaza towards Israeli communities surrounding Gaza.[918]
  • An Israeli soldier who was a sniper in the Kfir Brigade was killed by a sniper in Beit Lahia.[919][920]
  • The IDF said that its soldiers killed numerous militants, dismantled militant infrastructure sites, and located a large amount of weapons during their operation in Rafah in the last day.[921]
  • The NNA reported that Israeli soldiers reached their deepest point in Lebanon by capturing a strategic hill in Chamaa before retreating after intense clashes with Hezbollah fighters.[922] Hezbollah said that its fighters ambushed Israeli soldiers in Chamaa and claimed to have inflicted casualties.[923]
  • An Israeli strike in al-Khraiba, Baalbek region killed at least six people including three children and injured 11 others including five children.[924]
  • Dozens of Israeli settlers burned Palestinian properties in Beit Furik.[925]
  • The Houthis said that it attacked a "vital target" in Eilat using drones.[926]
  • Hezbollah claimed to have set an Israeli Merkava tank in Chamaa on fire using a guided missile.[927]
  • A Hezbollah rocket barrage hit a synagogue in Haifa. The IDF said that it wounded two civilians. However, Magen David Adom said that it located "no victims" from rocket shrapnel, while five civilians were mildly wounded while rushing to shelter. Hezbollah said that it targeted IDF bases in Haifa and its vicinity.[928][929]
  • A Palestinian journalist died from injuries sustained from an Israeli drone strike in Jabalia refugee camp.[930]
  • An Israeli strike hit a house in Shiyah neighborhood of Beirut, critically injuring a female Lebanese midfielder.[931]
  • A rocket launched from Lebanon hit an agricultural area in the vicinity of Tamra killing several animals and heavily damaging buildings and vehicles.[932]

17 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 47 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,846.[933][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 29 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon a day prior.[934]
  • An Israeli strike on a home in Bureij refugee camp killed at least 10 Palestinians including a child and injured several others including children. The IDF said that it is operating to dismantle military capabilities of Hamas.[935][936][937]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for three areas in the southern suburbs of Beirut including Burj el-Barajneh and Chiyah. The NNA reported that Israeli jets destroyed a 12-storey residential building in Chiyah. It also reported Israeli strikes in Burj el-Barajneh and Hadath.[938][939]
  • An Israeli strike on a home in Nuseirat refugee camp killing at least six Palestinians including four women and a child.[940]
  • An Israeli strike on a multi-storey residential building in Beit Lahia killed at least 50 people and dozens more were injured including children and trapped others under the debris. The IDF said that it carried out several strikes on militant targets in the area.[941][942][937]
  • The IDF said that it killed hundreds of militants during its operation in Beit Lahia, Beit Hanoun and Jabalia.[941]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for areas of Haret Hreik.[943]
  • At least two other children were killed in different areas across central Gaza.[944]
  • The Palestinian Authority's Minister of Transport and Communications Tariq Zourob said that at least 300,000 tonnes of "solid waste" are reportedly on the streets in the Gaza.[945]
  • An Israeli strike on a building containing the headquarters of the Lebanese branch of the Ba'ath Party in Ras al-Nabaa neighborhood of Beirut Central District killed Mohammad Afif, media relations chief of Hezbollah.[946][947] The Lebanese Health Ministry said that a total of seven people were killed including a woman and 16 others were injured including two children in the strike.[948][949][950] Hezbollah confirmed that four other members of its media relations department died alongside Afif.[951]
  • An Israeli strike hit a Lebanese Army post in al-Mari, Hasbaya District, killing two Lebanese soldiers and injuring three others, one of them seriously.[952]
  • Two soldiers of the Kfir brigade, including a nephew of former IDF Chief of Staff Gadi Eisenkot, were killed and another was seriously wounded in a firefight with Hamas operatives in Beit Lahia, bringing the IDF death toll in Gaza to 378.[953][920]
  • The Houthis claimed to have successfully conducted drone strikes on a number of IDF and other "vital targets" in Jaffa and Ashkelon.[954]
  • The Gaza Civil Defense Agency said that an Israeli drone targeted a group of unarmed people waiting for aid, killing six Palestinians in Khan Yunis.[955]
  • An Israeli airstrike on an electronics store in the Mar Elias, Beirut killed three people including a woman and injured 29 others.[956][957]
  • A 13-year-old boy was wounded after Hezbollah fired 15 rockets towards northern Israel.[958]
  • Hezbollah claimed to have inflicted casualties on crew of an Israeli Merkava tank in the Tyre Harfa-Jbeen triangle by destroying it using a guided missile.[959]

18 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 76 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,922.[960][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 35 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon a day prior.[961]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it launched a drone strike on a "vital target" in Eilat.[962]
  • Israeli strikes on an Islamic Health Association Centre in Houmine El Tahta and a health centre in the village of Hanaway killed two paramedics. Another Israeli strike on an ambulance center in Bazouriyeh injured two more paramedics.[963]
  • An Israeli strike on a tent sheltering displaced people in Israeli-designated safe zone of al-Mawasi, Khan Yunis killed at least five people including two children and injured several others including a child.[964][965][966]
  • Palestinian fighters clashed with Israeli forces in Balata refugee camp.[967]
  • Israeli strikes in Nabatieh Governorate killed at least six paramedics.[968]
  • Families of American victims of the 7 October attacks filed a lawsuit in a district court in Washington DC accusing Iran of culpability in the Hamas-led attack due to its funding of Hamas.[969]
  • An Israeli strike on a home in the vicinity of al-Jalaa Street in the west of the Gaza City killed seven people including three children and two women and wounded several others.[970][971]
  • Israeli soldiers seized four water networks owned by Palestinian farmers in Khirbet al-Deir.[972]
  • An Israeli strike on a home in the vicinity of Kamal Adwan Hospital killed at least 17 people.[973]
  • Israeli soldiers fired on a vehicle in Masafer Yatta, injuring a Palestinian woman on her hand. The IDF said that woman attempted to run over soldiers.[974][975]
  • An Israeli strike in Nuseirat refugee camp killed four people, including a woman and a child.[966]
  • A Hezbollah rocket struck a multi-story building in Shfar'am killing a woman and injuring 10 others. Separate rocket barrages on northern Israel injured two people.[976]
  • In the evening, a Hezbollah missile hit exactly on the administrative border between Ramat Gan and Bnei Brak in front of one of the towers in a district of high-rise office towers, injuring six people, one seriously. It was later reported that an IDF interceptor hit that missile at high altitude but failed to detonate it.[977][978][979]
  • The Gaza interior ministry said that security forces in cooperation with tribal committees killed over 20 gang members involved in stealing UN aid trucks in the Gaza. UN spokesman Stephane Dujarric said that only 11 of the 109 trucks in the convoy reached their destination.[980]
  • The IDF announced that an airstrike in southern Lebanon killed the commander of Hezbollah's medium-range rocket unit.[981][982]

19 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 50 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,972.[983][a] The Gaza Government Media Office said that 17,492 of the dead were children.[984]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 28 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon a day prior.[985]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said it launched a drone strike on a "vital target" in southern Israel.[986]
  • Hezbollah rockets damaged several houses and vehicles in Kiryat Shmona.[987]
  • Palestinian armed groups clashed with Israeli forces in Jenin and the Jenin refugee camp. The Jenin Brigades said that it targeted an IDF bulldozer using an explosive device. The IDF said that it killed at least three Palestinian gunmen.[988][989]
  • A Hezbollah rocket strike injured seven people in central Israel.[990]
  • Israeli artillery shelling hit a house in the vicinity of Nuseirat refugee camp, killing an infant.[991]
  • The director of Kamal Adwan Hospital, Hussam Abu Safiya said that malnutrition cases had started to arrive at the hospital, mostly children and the elderly, because of famine.[992]
  • The Israel Border Police said it had fired at a suspicious man in the Shuafat checkpoint north of Jerusalem, moderately injuring him.[993]
  • A reservist of the Golani Brigade's logistics unit was killed and three others were seriously injured in a Hezbollah drone strike in southern Lebanon, increasing the IDF death toll since the invasion of Lebanon to 53.[994]
  • The IDF said that it conducted more than 150 strikes against Hezbollah targets throughout Lebanon including 25 weapons depots and approximately 30 rocket launchers since 17 November.[995]
  • An Israeli strike on a group of Palestinians queuing for water in front of a school in Beit Lahia killed a child and wounded eight others. Another Israeli strike in Gaza City killed a Palestinian journalist.[996]
  • The Houthis said that they launched a missile strike towards a vessel in Red Sea. Later, the Turkish Foreign Ministry denounced Houthi missile strikes on Panama-flagged dry cargo ship Anadolu S, belonging to a Turkish company, while sailing near the coast of Yemen.[997][998]
  • Israeli forces demolished Al-Shiyah Mosque in Jabal Mukaber neighbourhood of East Jerusalem after issuing a demolition order.[999]
  • The Al-Quds Brigades said that it targeted a group of Israeli soldiers and vehicles using mortar shells near Jabalia Services Club, in the center of Jabalia refugee camp.[1000]
  • The UNIFIL said that four Ghanaian peacekeepers were injured when a rocket that was most likely launched by "non-state actors" hit their base in Ramyah.[1001] In a separate incident, eight rockets struck an Italian UNIFIL headquarters in Chamaa. The IDF blamed Hezbollah for both attacks.[1002]
  • An Israeli airstrike hit a Lebanese Army position in Sarafand killing three soldiers and injuring 17 others, including civilians.[1003][1004][1005]
  • The Palestine Red Crescent Society said that Israeli soldiers used Palestinian paramedics as human shields in the West Bank.[1006]
  • The Al-Quds Brigades said that it targeted Israeli soldiers using mortar rounds south of Juhor ad-Dik.[1007]
  • An Israeli air strike on a residential building in Beit Lahia killed at least eight Palestinians, injured several others and trapped several others under the debris. Witnesses said that it was housing members of a family and displaced civilians.[1008]
  • The IDF destroyed water tanks and sewage systems in Kamal Adwan Hospital for the 10th time.[1009] Israel's Coordinator of Government Activities in the Territories said that it send 1,000 units of blood to Kamal Adwan Hospital, which the UN health cluster confirmed.[1003]
  • The French foreign ministry announced that an UN peacekeeping patrol in Lebanon comprising French soldiers came under fire.[1010]

20 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 13 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 43,985.[1011][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 14 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon a day prior.[1012]
  • An Israeli air strike in Jabalia al-Balad killed 12 Palestinians and at least 10 others went missing.[1013][1014]
  • An Israeli strike destroyed the roof and upper floors of a building of Kamal Adwan Hospital.[1015]
  • Israeli forces raided Jenin, triggering clashes with Palestinian fighters.[1016]
  • Israeli settlers set fire to cars owned by Palestinians in al-Mazraa al-Gharbiya village in the West Bank.[1017]
  • An Israeli strike in Sabra neighborhood of Gaza City killed a Gaza Civil Defense worker and injured three Gaza Civil Defense workers and an Al Jazeera journalist.[1013][1018][1019][1020]
  • The NNA reported that Hezbollah fighters destroyed an Israeli Merkava tank in Al Bayyadah town in the vicinity of Naqoura.[1021]
  • Wafa reported that Israeli soldiers arrested seven Palestinians including a 11-year-old boy from the West Bank. It also reported that they confiscated a vehicle and vandalised property while raiding houses in Abu Falah.[1022]
  • An Israeli soldier from the Nahshon Battalion of the Kfir Brigade was killed, while the commander of the Nahshon Battalion was critically wounded while fighting in northern Gaza.[1023]
  • An Israeli strike hit a Lebanese army vehicle in a road between Burj al-Muluk and Al-Qlaiaah, killing a Lebanese soldier and injuring another.[1024][1025]
  • Kamal Adwan Hospital director Hussam Abu Safiya said that an elderly man died due to starvation in northern Gaza.[1026]
  • Israeli strikes in Palmyra killed 108 Iran-backed fighters, including four from Hezbollah, and injured 21 others including seven civilians.[1027][1028]
  • Israeli shelling in Khirbet al-Adas town in the vicinity of Rafah killed at least two people including an elderly man and injured several others.[1029]
  • The IDF announced that it attacked over 100 Hezbollah targets in Lebanon including launchers, facilities used for storing weapons, command centres, and military structures one day prior. It also announced that the IAF killed the commanders of its anti-tank missile unit and operations unit in the coastal area on 17 November.[1030]
  • An Israeli air strike in Israeli-designated humanitarian zone of al-Mawasi in Khan Yunis killed seven Palestinians including three children.[1031][1032]
  • During a shootout with two Hezbollah militants, a soldier and Zhabo Erlich, an armed civilian researcher wearing an IDF uniform were both killed. Erlich had entered southern Lebanon in breach of IDF procedures, accompanied by the Golani Brigade's chief of staff Col. Yarom, reportedly to see the Chamaa fortress. Two others were injured, namely the brigade's chief of staff and a company commander from the brigade's 13th Battalion. Both militants were also killed. Erlich was posthumously given a military rank.[1033][1034][1035]
  • A reservist from the Maglan commando unit was killed following a building collapse in southern Lebanon.[1036][1037]
  • An Israeli strike in Sheikh Radwan neighbourhood of Gaza City killed 22 people, including 10 children.[1038]
  • An Israeli strike on a residential neighbourhood in Beit Lahia in the vicinity of Kamal Adwan Hospital killed 66 people, mostly women and children, injured over 100 others and trapped three disabled people including a blind girl under the debris.[1039][1040][1041]
  • Hezbollah fired a barrage of 25 rockets at the western Galilee, with one striking a kindergarten fence in Acre.[1042]
  • An Israeli strike on a school serving as shelter for displaced people in the Nuseirat refugee camp killed seven people including two women and three children.[1043]

21 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 71 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,056. The IDF said that it killed more than 17,000 militants, without offering evidence.[1044][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 25 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon a day prior.[1045]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents for Tyre, as well as Burj al-Shamali, Mashouq and al-Haush villages in Tyre district to move to north of the Awali river. Israeli warplanes then struck al-Haush and Tyre.[1046][1047][1048]
  • Senator Bernie Sanders introduced three resolutions in the US Senate for halting the sale of some US weapons for Israel which failed to pass, garnering 20 votes among its 100 members.[1049]
  • Israeli authorities charged three Palestinians accused of planning to assassinate the far-right Israeli National Security Minister Itamar Ben Gvir.[1050]
  • An Israeli quadcopter strike injured six Palestinians, including two children in the Bureij refugee camp.[1051]
  • The IDF issued two evacuation orders for residents of Hadath and Haret Hreik, including one centred on three buildings. At least 12 Israeli strikes hit Haret Hreik.[1052][1053][1054]
  • The IDF said that it killed nine militants during a two-day raid in Jenin. It claimed that those killed were participants in attacks on Israeli communities, IDF sites or soldiers. It added that it destroyed dozens of explosives and four explosive laboratories, and arrested several people suspected of militant activity.[1055]
  • A rocket strike from Lebanon killed a man in Nahariya.[1056]
  • An IDF soldier from the Givati Brigade was killed in Jabalia.[1057]
  • The International Criminal Court issued arrest warrants for the leader of the Al-Qassam Brigades, Mohammed Deif, Israeli prime minister Benjamin Netanyahu and former Israeli defence minister Yoav Gallant.[1058]
  • The IDF said that a ballistic missile was launched from Yemen towards Israel.[1059]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it launched a drone towards southern Israel.[1060]
  • Six medical staff of Kamal Adwan Hospital were wounded, including one seriously after being hit by grenades dropped by an Israeli drone when they rushed to its emergency gate where a group of people were hit by an Israeli strike. Its water tanks and oxygen station were also significantly damaged.[1061]
  • The Gaza Civil Defense Agency said that 15 children and women were hospitalized after being poisoned by eating canned food allegedly left behind by Israeli soldiers in Shujaiya neighbourhood of Gaza City.[1062]

22 November

  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 62 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon a day prior.[1063]
  • An Israeli air strike hit a tent serving as shelter for displaced people in al-Mawasi, killing a woman, her daughter and another child.[1064][1065]
  • Palestinian armed groups said that they opened fire and set off explosive devices targeting Israeli soldiers during their raid in the Old City of Nablus.[1066]
  • Three people were wounded in a stampede while people rushed to bomb shelters in Haifa and Krayot after five rockets crossed into northern Israel from Lebanon.[1067]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for civilians in Taybeh, Aadshit al-Qusayr and Deir Siriane to immediately move to the northern side of the Awali river.[1068]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents of Borj El Chmali, Ma’shouq and a number of buildings in Haret Hreik. Later, Israeli fighter jets launched four strikes targeting Haret Hreik and al-Hadath in Beirut's southern suburbs.[1069][1070]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents of buildings near a building highlighted for strike in Tyre. Later, an Israeli strike hit the building.[1071][1072]
  • The IDF and Shin Bet claimed to have killed five Hamas militants including Jihad Mahmoud Yahya Kahlout, a Nukhba forces company commander, and Muhammad Riad Ali Oukal, a Hamas company commander who participated in the 7 October attack in an air strike in Beit Lahia one day prior. Hamas said that Israeli attacks in Beit Lahia killed a total of 112 people, including 64 children and women.[1073][1074]
  • The IDF and Shin Bet claimed to have killed Khalid Abu Daqqa, commander of PIJ's rocket unit responsible for launching rockets towards Israel during the 7 October attack and during the war who participated in many other attacks on Israel and Israeli soldiers in a strike in Deir al-Balah. The IDF also claimed that he operated from the Israeli-designated humanitarian zone in Deir al-Balah.[1075][1076]
  • An Israeli strike hit a fishing boat near the coast of Gaza City, killing a Palestinian fisherman and injuring another.[1077]
  • The Gaza Health Ministry said that Kamal Adwan Hospital ran out of electricity and oxygen after Israeli strikes hit its oxygen station and generators.[1078][1079] An infant died in an incubator due to the shortage.[1080]
  • An Israeli strike hit an ambulance in Deir Qanoun Ras al-Ain, killing two Hezbollah affiliated paramedics.[1081][1082]
  • Israeli defence minister Israel Katz announced an end to the use of administrative detention against Israeli settlers in the West Bank.[1083]
  • The IDF said that its airstrikes in southern Lebanon destroyed approximately 45 Hezbollah rocket launchers in this week.[1084]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents in Mansouri, Iskenderun, Majdal Zoun, Bayut Al-Sayyad Farm and Al-Haush in Lebanon to move to the north of the Awali river and issued another evacuation order for Chiyah, highlighting two buildings. An Israeli missile destroyed a multistory building in Chiyah.[1085][1086]
  • Israeli strikes in Qatrani, Jezzine District killed three paramedics from the Islamic Health Association.[1087]
  • Two rockets likely fired by Hezbollah hit a UNIFIL base in Chamaa, slightly injuring at least four Italian peacekeepers.[1088][1089]
  • Hezbollah claimed that its drone hit Israeli forces in Yarin.[1090]
  • The Gaza Health Ministry said that all hospitals in Gaza will stop or cut services within two days due to lack of fuel.[1091]
  • Hezbollah claimed to have forced an Israeli warplane to leave Lebanese airspace by confronting it using "appropriate weapons” opposite Sidon.[1092]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for all residents of Hadath, Haret Hreik and Ghobeiry, highlighting three buildings.[1093]
  • The IDF said that its fighter jets launched a wave of strikes on Hezbollah targets including command headquarters, intelligence infrastructure, weapons depots, observation posts and military buildings in Tyre.[1094]
  • An Israeli strike in the Baalbek area killed seven people including the director-general of Dar al-Amal University Hospital.[1095]
  • The IDF entered the town of Deir Mimas and set up road blocks around the area with heavy clashes reported.[1096]
  • An Israeli airstrike in Syria killed Ali Musa Daqduq, a senior Hezbollah militant and one of the planners of a raid in 2007 that killed five US soldiers during the Iraq War.[1097]
  • Hezbollah fired approximately 80 rockets at northern Israel.[1098]

23 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 120 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 48 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,176.[1099][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 25 people were killed in Israeli attacks in Lebanon a day prior.[1100]
  • At least seven people, including children were killed and several others were injured in an Israeli strike on a building in the Zeitoun neighbourhood of Gaza City.[1101]
  • Palestinian fighters targeted Israeli forces using an explosive device in the old Askar Camp.[1102]
  • Israeli soldiers assaulted Palestinian paramedics in Osarin and detained a female paramedic.[1103]
  • At least nine people including children was killed in an Israeli strike in the Sheikh Nasser area, east of Khan Yunis.[1104]
  • Hezbollah released two photos of what it claimed as its guided missiles hitting two Israeli tanks.[1105]
  • An Israeli airstrike on a building in Basta area of Beirut Central District targeting Hezbollah official Muhammad Haydar killed at least 29 people and injured 67 others including women.[1106][1107][1108] The target was reportedly not present in the building.[1109] The IDF claimed to have struck a command center of Hezbollah.[1110]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents in parts of Hadath, Choueifat and Al-Amrousieh to move at least 500 metres. Israeli forces conducted strikes in Hadath and in Choueifat approximately one hour later.[1111][1112][1113]
  • An Israeli drone strike killed two fishermen in Tyre.[1114]
  • Israeli settlers attacked Palestinian houses in the outskirts of the al-Dubbat neighbourhood of Beit Furik.[1115]
  • An Israeli artillery strike killed three people including a woman and her child in Bureij refugee camp.[1116]
  • The IDF detained 15 Palestinians including minors from the West Bank in the past two days.[1117]
  • A bombardment hit Kamal Adwan Hospital, resulting in 12 injuries among hospital staff. The IDF denied responsibility for the attack.[1118][1119]
  • Hezbollah claimed to have inflicted casualties on Israeli soldiers heading towards al-Bayada.[1120]
  • Hezbollah claimed to have hit Israeli soldiers in Deir Mimas and Khiam using rockets and missiles in three separate strikes.[1121]
  • The IDF said that it killed a group of Hamas militants including a sniper in Jabalia and released the footage of its strike on a building housing the sniper. It said that it also destroyed Hamas infrastructure and located dozens of weapons.[1122]
  • Two rockets were launched from the southern side of Deir el-Balah towards Israel.[1123]
  • Israeli forces arrested two people, including a minor from Kafr Abbush.[1124]
  • Hamas claimed that an Israeli female hostage was killed and another Israeli female hostage was seriously injured in an area attacked by Israeli forces in northern Gaza.[1125][1126]
  • An Israeli air strike on a residence in Shmestar killed eight people, including four children, and wounded nine others, four of them seriously.[1127]
  • A group of Israeli settlers stormed an Islamic cemetery in Hebron. They also marched through the Old City of Hebron, climbed to rooftops of residents and yelled slurs, such as "Death to Arabs". A settler threw a rock in the direction of a Palestinian documenting the incident.[1128]
  • The al-Qassam Brigades said that it targeted an IDF engineering infantry force consisting of five soldiers using an antipersonnel shell and hit an armoured troop carrier using a Yassin-105 shell in the vicinity of the Burj Awad junction in Rafah. It also said that Palestinian fighters hit a Nimr armoured vehicle in the as-Saftawi area north of Gaza City and launched an anti-fortification shell towards soldiers holed up in a home in the area.[1129]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for several neighbourhoods in Khan Yunis, saying that rockets were launched from the area towards Israel.[1130]
  • At least five Israeli settlers suspected of chasing Central Command Major-General Avi Bluth and Israeli soldiers accompanying him, were arrested in Hebron. Israeli settlers also threw stones at soldiers in the vicinity of Nablus and an Israeli settler punched a soldier after they stole a vehicle of Palestinians. Five settlers were arrested in that incident.[1131]
  • Hezbollah claimed that it shelled Israeli forces in Chamaa.[1132]
  • SANA reported that Israeli forces targeted the Jusiyah crossing in al-Qusayr, Syria, causing minor material damage.[1133][1134]
  • The IDF claimed that it hit a Hezbollah military headquarters in Dahieh.[1135]
  • Hezbollah claimed that it inflicted casualties among the crew of two Merkava tanks using guided missiles on the eastern outskirts of al-Bayada[1136] and Al Jabin. Hezbollah claimed that its drone hit the headquarters of the Golani Brigade Command, north of Acre.[1137]
  • Israel settlers from Havat Maon outpost attacked the house of Palestinian activist Hafez al-Harini in Tuwanah village in Masafer Yatta, injuring two people. Israeli soldiers who backed the settlers arrested Harini. Another attack on a house in a village in the same area extensively damaged property.[1138][1139]
  • An Israeli air strike in Ain Baal killed at least two people and injured four paramedics.[1140]
  • The al-Qassam Brigades released a video showing detonation of an improvised explosive device in the vicinity of a raiding IDF vehicle in the West Bank.[1141]
  • A soldier from the Golani Brigade's 13th Battalion was seriously injured in southern Lebanon.[1142]
  • An Israeli strike in Khan Yunis killed at least seven people including three Palestinian children and wounded another person.[1143]
  • Shrapnel from a bomb dropped by an Israeli quadcopter injured Hussam Abu Safia, director of Kamal Adwan Hospital on his leg.[1144]

24 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 35 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,211.[1145][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 84 people were killed in the latest reporting period of 24 hours.[1146]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for Shujayea neighborhood of Gaza City.[1147]
  • An Israeli strike on a home in Bureij refugee camp killed four people including two children.[1148]
  • Israeli soldiers opened fire during a raid in the Balata refugee camp, injuring a Palestinian boy.[1149]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents of East Zotar, West Zotar, Arnoun, Yahmar and Al-Qasiba.[1150]
  • A gunman wounded three Jordanian police officers by firing at a police patrol in the vicinity of the Israeli embassy in Amman. The gunman was shot dead by police.[1151]
  • An Israeli strike on a residential building in Nuseirat refugee camp killed six people including children.[1152]
  • Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's office announced that Zvi Kogan, an Israeli man who went missing in UAE, was found murdered. His office condemned his death as a "heinous antisemitic terrorist act".[1153] UAE arrested three people suspected in his killing.[1154]
  • A Israeli strike hit a Lebanese army centre in Al-Amiriya on the Al-Qalila-Tyre road killing a Lebanese soldier and injuring 18 others.[1155] The IDF apologized for the attack.[1156]
  • At least 250 rockets were launched from Lebanon towards Israel.[1157] There were at least six instances of direct impact in five different places, including two IDF sites. Totally, some 10 Israelis were wounded, including one critically.[1158][1159]
  • The IDF called residents in parts of the southern suburbs of Beirut to evacuate. Israeli strikes hit the Kafaat area approximately an hour later.[1160]
  • The al-Qassam Brigades said that it targeted an IDF vehicle containing an infantry group of 10 soldiers north of Awad Tower in Rafah using a 105mm al-Yassin rocket and inflicted casualties.[1161]
  • Al Jazeera reported that Hezbollah fighters forced the IDF to retreat from the strategic al-Bayyaada hill.[1162]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents in certain buildings in Ghobeiry and Bourj el-Barajneh. Later, Israeli strikes hit the area.[1163][1164]
  • The IDF claimed that it struck 12 Hezbollah military headquarters including its intelligence headquarters and its coastal missile unit.[1165]
  • Hezbollah claimed to have destroyed destroyed six Merkava tanks in southern Lebanon.[1166]
  • Israeli strikes hit the Kamal Adwan Hospital for a seventh consecutive day.[1167]
  • The Netanyahu government sanctioned Israeli left wing newspaper Haaretz for publishing articles critical of the war in Gaza.[1168]
  • The Islamic Resistance in Iraq said that it fired two drone strikes on targets in southern Israel.[1169]

25 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 24 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,235.[1170][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 14 people were killed in the past 24 hours.[1171]
  • Israeli forces shot dead two people including a 13 year old Palestinian boy in Ya'bad.[1172]
  • The IDF claimed that in coordination with Shin Bet, it killed Halim Abu Hussein, a key Hamas militant in a battalion in western Jabalia who was responsible for many attacks against Israeli soldiers operating in Gaza with rockets and mortars and several other Hamas militants in a strike in the weekend.[1173]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents of Halta to move to areas north of the Awali River.[1174]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents in Haret Hreik. Later, the IDF conducted air strikes in the area, saying that it hit several Hezbollah command centres.[1175][1176]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents of four buildings in Beirut's southern suburbs. Later, Israeli air strikes hit the area.[1177][1178] The IDF said that its strikes in Nabatieh, Baalbek, the Beqaa Valley, southern Beirut and its outskirts hit approximately 25 Hezbollah targets including its Executive Council's command centres, and intelligence control and collection centres containing Hezbollah commanders and operatives.[1179]
  • Two people were wounded from shrapnel after Hezbollah launched a barrage of 20 rockets at the Upper and Western Galilee.[1180] Two others were wounded, one woman seriously, when ten rockets were fired at Nahariya.[1181]
  • The Al-Quds Brigades claimed that it destroyed an Israeli Merkava tank in the Aslan area, west of Beit Lahia using an explosive device.[1182]
  • The Gaza Government Media Office said that approximately 10,000 tents were washed away or damaged because of winter storms.[1183]
  • SANA reported that Israeli strikes hit several bridges in Al-Qusayr, injuring at least two civilians and causing material losses. The IDF said that it targeted what it says as routes used by Hezbollah for smuggling Iranian weapons. It also said that it is part of efforts against Unit 4400 of Hezbollah, which is responsible for delivering weapons from Iran and its proxies to Lebanon, through Syria and Iraq.[1184][1185][1186]

26 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 14 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,249.[1187][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 55 people were killed in Israeli attacks the past 24 hours.[1188]
  • An Israeli strike in az-Zarqa area of Gaza City killed six people including women and children.[1189]
  • Palestinian fighters fired on Israeli forces during an IDF raid in Jenin. Confrontations erupted between Israeli soldiers and Palestinians during an IDF raid in Balata refugee camp.[1190]
  • A drone was launched from the east towards the Golan Heights.[1191]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents of Beit Lahia, saying that it is becoming an active military war zone.[1192]
  • Israeli soldiers raided Birzeit University and arrested students participating in a protest.[1193]
