  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents in Laylaki, Choueifat and parts of Ghobeiry, Bourj el-Barajneh and Tahouitet al-Ghadir. Later, Israeli air strikes were reported in the area. The IDF claimed to have struck six Hezbollah targets.[1194][1195][1196][1197]
  • The Gaza Civil Defense Agency said that it ceased its work in Gaza City after it ran out of diesel.[1198]
  • The IDF arrested 16 Palestinians, including two minors from the West Bank. According to the Palestinian Prisoners’ Society, soldiers damaged the houses of those arrested and threatened them and their families.[1199]
  • Israeli forces from the 91st Division raided Hezbollah sites on the eastern part of the Litani River and the Wadi Saluki area.[1200]
  • An Israeli soldier from the 8163rd engineering battalion was critically injured during combat in central Gaza. Another female Israeli soldier was seriously injured by a Hezbollah drone attack in Mount Meron.[1201]
  • The IDF announced that Ahmed Subhi Hazima, the head of Hezbollah's operations in Lebanon's coastal sector, was killed in an airstrike in Tyre. It claimed that he helped to plan infiltration plans into Israeli territory and was involved in launching antitank missiles towards the western Galilee.[1202][1203]
  • An Israeli strike on Al-Hurreya School serving as shelter for displaced people in the Zeitoun neighbourhood of Gaza City killed at least 13 people and injured over 40 others. The IDF said that it struck Hamas militants operating in a command and control center embedded inside the compound.[1204][1205][1206]
  • The IDF said that it struck approximately 30 Hezbollah targets including a launcher used for firing projectiles towards Israel the previous day, facilities used for storing weapons, militant infrastructure sites, command centres, and additional launchers.[1207]
  • The IDF said that it conducted a wave of strikes on 20 Hezbollah targets including 13 targets in Dahieh including an aerial defence unit centre, an intelligence centre, command centre, facilities used for storing weapons and claimed that other targets were components of financial system of Hezbollah.[1208]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents in parts of Tyre and Sidon to move at least 500 metres.[1209]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents of Baalbek, Kasarnaba and parts of Hadath.[1210]
  • SANA reported that Israeli jets conducted an air strike on two villages in Homs Governorate.[1211]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents of four locations in Central Beirut for the first time since the start of the conflict. Later, Israeli strikes were reported in the area.[1212]
  • Israel approved a ceasefire with Hezbollah.[1213]
  • A soldier of the Kfir Brigade was killed fighting in Gaza, increasing the IDF death toll in Gaza to 381.[1206]
  • The IDF said that it killed Basel Kamel Salim Nabahin, a PIJ militant who participated in the 7 October attack in an airstrike in southern Gaza.[1206]
  • Lebanese transport minister Ali Hamieh said that Israeli strikes hit the Arida, Dabousieh and Jussiyeh border crossings with Syria.[1214] Syrian state media reported that four civilians and two soldiers were killed, and 12 people were injured including children, women and workers in the Syrian Red Crescent.[1215][1216] The IDF claimed that it struck several "smuggling routes" into Syria used by Hezbollah for funneling its weapons.[1217]
  • Hezbollah claimed that its drones hit IAF chief Tomer Bar's residence in Tel Aviv and other sensitive IDF targets in Tel Aviv and its suburbs.[1218]

27 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 33 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,282.[1219][a]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents of central and southern Beirut including in Ghobeiry.[1220]
  • The IDF claimed that it hit 330 Hezbollah sites throughout Lebanon in the night leading up to the truce, including command centres, weapons depots, infrastructure used by the Radwan Force, and an underground precision missile plant. The IDF estimated that it killed several dozens of Hezbollah operatives in its strikes on a Radwan Force base in Beqaa Valley.[1221] It also claimed that it killed an operations officer from Hezbollah's aerial unit in a strike in Beirut.[1222]
  • The ceasefire deal between Israel and Hezbollah went into effect at 4:00 a.m. UTC+02:00.[1223]
  • The IDF arrested 15 Palestinians including a minor from the West Bank. The Palestinian Prisoner's Society said that soldiers damaged many houses while making the arrests.[1224]
  • The IDF opened fire at people attempting to return to southern Lebanon, hitting several in Mais al-Jabal. It later announced that it killed an unspecified number of militants.[1225]
  • An Israeli strike on al-Tabin school in Gaza City killed at least 13 people including six women, two sons of a Hamas official and children.[1226][1227][1228]
  • Israeli soldiers opened fire on journalists covering the withdrawal of Israeli forces and the return of displaced residents to Khiam, injuring two of them.[1229][1230]
  • The IDF said that it arrested four suspects who approached Israeli soldiers in southern Lebanon.[1231][1232]
  • The IDF imposed a curfew in southern Lebanon until 7:00 a.m. UTC+02:00 the next day, saying that it was still deployed in its positions in southern Lebanon according to the terms of the ceasefire agreement, and its forces will deal firmly with any movement that violates this agreement.[1233][1234]
  • Al Jazeera reported that two civilian were killed in an Israeli bombardment in al-Qarara.[1235]
  • An Israeli strike on a home in al-Faluga area of Jabalia refugee camp killed four people including a pregnant woman.[1236][1237]
  • The IDF said that it killed Morad Rajab, a Hamas militant in Gaza City.[1226]
  • The IDF claimed that it hit dozens of military structures of Hamas including sites used for fighting and storing weapons in northern Gaza.[1226]
  • The IDF claimed that it shot down a drone used for smuggling weapons from Egypt containing four guns, five cartridges and hundreds of bullets which crossed from Egypt to Israel. Egyptian security sources said that they are unaware of such an incident.[1238][1239]
  • Shrapnel from live bullets fired by Israeli soldiers during their raid in Faqqua wounded a child. Clashes erupted in Faqqua after Israeli soldiers raided it.[1240]
  • Israeli soldiers fired at people returning to their houses and villages in Lebanon, killing at least six people and injuring many others.[1241]

28 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 48 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,330.[1242][a] Israel claimed to have killed approximately 20,000 militants.[1243]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry announced that 78 people were killed in Israeli attacks two days prior.[1244] The IDF claimed to have killed around 3,500 Hezbollah fighters.[1245]
  • The Tulkarm Brigade claimed that it inflicted casualties on Israeli forces by detonating an explosive device in an IDF vehicle and opening fire on Israeli forces in Jabal an-Nasr.[1246]
  • Israeli shelling hit a house in Zeitoun, Gaza City, killing a Palestinian child.[1247]
  • An Israeli drone strike in the vicinity of a camp for displaced people in Abasan killed four people including civilians and wounded several others.[1248]
  • Israeli soldiers fired on Markaba, injuring two people.[1249]
  • An Israeli tank targeted the outskirts of Kfarchouba in Lebanon using two shells.[1250]
  • An Israeli strike in the Nuseirat refugee camp wounded Talal al-Arouqi, a correspondent for Al Jazeera Mubasher, and flying shrapnel killed another person.[1251][1252]
  • The IDF said that the ceasefire was violated with the arrival of suspects, some of them with vehicles, at several areas in southern Lebanon.[1253]
  • The IDF carried out an airstrike on a rocket depot in southern Lebanon after identifying Hezbollah activity there.[1254]
  • The IDF prohibited travel within and towards the south of the Litani River from 5:00 p.m. UTC+02:00 until 7:00 a.m. UTC+02:00 the next day.[1255]
  • The Houthi-affiliated Al-Masirah TV news reported two US-UK air strikes in Bajil District.[1256]
  • An Israeli drone strike killed an elderly man in the Nuseirat refugee camp.[1257]
  • An Israeli strike on a tent housing displaced people in Khan Yunis killed four people including a child and injured several others.[1258]
  • The IDF warned residents to not return to 62 villages in southern Lebanon.[1259][1260]

29 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 33 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,363.[1261][a]
  • An Israeli strike hit two houses near Abu Diya Bakery, west of Gaza City, killing four people including two women and a child and injuring several others.[1262]
  • Wafa reported that the IDF raided a home in southern Hebron and destroyed its contents.[1263]
  • At a bus stop near the Giti Avisar junction, in the vicinity of the illegal settlement of Ariel, a gunman opened fire at a bus and then exchanged fire with Israeli soldiers who were present at the bus stop. He was shot dead by the soldiers. Three people including the bus driver were seriously wounded while at least six other people, including four soldiers, suffered lesser injuries.[1264][1265][1266][1267] The al-Qassam Brigades claimed responsibility.[1268][1269]
  • In two instances, Palestinian gunmen shot at Israeli security services (IDF and border police) in the West Bank; in both cases there were no injuries and the gunmen managed to escape.[1270]
  • The NNA reported that four Israeli tanks entered the western side of Khiam. It also reported that Israeli artillery shelled the outskirts of Markaba and Talloussah.[1271][1272][1273] Footage released by Lebanese media showed Israeli soldiers in Khiam firing at several people while they were attempting to attend a funeral despite prior approval from the Lebanese army and UNIFIL to visit.[1274]
  • Two children and a woman died in a stampede outside a bakery in Gaza.[1275][1276]
  • An Israeli quadcopter strike killed Ahmed el-Kahlout, the head of the intensive care unit of Kamal Adwan Hospital, while he was on his way to the hospital.[1277]
  • The World Food Programme said that all bakeries in central Gaza were forced to close because of severe shortages in supplies.[1278]
  • Two Israeli strikes in Beit Lahia including one on a residential building killed 75 people and injured several others. Hamas said that most of those killed were women and children.[1279][1280]
  • The IDF said that it struck a Hezbollah rocket launcher in southern Lebanon.[1281]
  • An Israeli strike on a home in the Abu Iskandar area of Sheikh Radwan neighbourhood in Gaza City killed at least 10 people including civilians.[1282][1283]
  • Clashes erupted between Palestinian fighters and Israeli soldiers in the as-Saftawi area of northern Gaza.[1284]

30 November

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 19 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,382.[1285][a]
  • Nine Palestinians including a child were killed and 37 others including 12 children were wounded during IDF raids in the West Bank in the past two days.[1286]
  • The IDF prohibited residents from returning to dozens more villages in southern Lebanon until further notice.[1287]
  • An Israeli strike hit a car on the Salah al-Din Road in Khan Yunis killing five people. Three of those killed were employees of World Central Kitchen, and another was an employee of Save the Children. The IDF said that one of the dead had participated in the 7 October attack.[1288][1289][1290]
  • An Israeli strike on a residential flat in the Remal neighbourhood of Gaza City killed seven people including civilians and trapped six others under the debris.[1291]
  • An Israeli airstrike on a vehicle in Majdal Zoun in Lebanon wounded three people including a seven-year-old child.[1292] Another strike was reported south of Sidon, in Baisariyeh.[1293]
  • Three drones were launched from Iraq towards Israel.[1294][1295][1296]
  • An Israeli strike hit a house in the Jabalia refugee camp killing a Gaza civil defence member.[1297]
  • The IDF said that it had carried out an intelligence-based strike on border crossings used by Hezbollah for smuggling weapons from Syria to Lebanon.[1298]
  • An Israeli airstrike on a home in the Shujayea neighbourhood of eastern Gaza City killed seven people including a child and injured several others.[1299]
  • Hamas accused the IDF of using internationally prohibited weapons that vaporize bodies after collecting testimonies from doctors and residents in northern Gaza and demanded an international investigation.[1300]
  • The World Central Kitchen halted its distribution of meals in Gaza after the killing of its employees.[1301]
  • The IDF said that it had located an Hezbollah weapons cache under a mosque in southern Lebanon and dispersed suspects approaching a restricted zone.[1302]
  • The IDF renewed travel bans within and towards the south of the Litani River from 5:00 p.m. UTC+02:00 until 7:00 a.m. UTC+02:00 the next day.[1303]
  • An Israeli drone strike in Rab Thalathin in Lebanon killed two people and wounded two others.[1304]
  • The al-Qassam Brigades said it targeted two Israeli Merkava tanks using al-Yassin 105 shells in the al-Janina neighborhood, east of Rafah.[1305]
  • An Israeli airstrike on a group of Palestinians waiting for receiving food from an aid convoy in Khan Yunis killed at least 12 Palestinians and injured several others.[1306]
  • A 10-year-old child died due to lack of oxygen and medical supplies in Al-Awda Hospital.[1307]
  • A health official in Gaza said that famine has spread to all of Gaza.[1308]
  • An anti-tank missile killed an Israeli soldier in Jabalia and critically injured another soldier. A soldier was critically injured during combat with Palestinian fighters in southern Gaza. Another soldier was seriously injured during an operational IDF activity in northern Israel on the border with Lebanon.[1309][1310]
  • More than 40 people including women and children were killed in an Israeli air raid on the Tel al-Zataar area of Jabalia which caused the collapse of a six-story building.[1311][1312][1313]
  • Israeli air strikes in the Nuseirat refugee camp killed six people including civilians and injured several others.[1314]
  • An Israeli drone strike in northern Gaza killed Mahmoud Almadhoun, chef and cofounder of Gaza Soup Kitchen.[1315]
  • The al-Qassam Brigades claimed to have killed the crew of an Israeli Merkava tank in the north of Gaza City by hitting it with a Shawaz device.[1316]

December 2024

1 December

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 47 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,429.[1317][a]
  • An Israeli strike hit a tent in the Muwasi area of Gaza, killing at least two children and injuring two others.[1318]
  • Israeli soldiers arrested two An-Najah National University students after raiding their homes in Burin, Nablus.[1319]
  • A ballistic missile was launched from Yemen towards Israel.[1320]
  • A 15-year-old child was injured on his head during an IDF raid in Anabta. The Palestinian Red Crescent Society said that a 15-year-old boy was injured and a 16-year-old was beaten by Israeli soldiers in Astra, West Bank where an IDF raid triggered clashes.[1321]
  • The IDF conducted drone strikes targeting Palestinian fighters in Jenin.[1322]
  • The UNRWA paused aid deliveries through the Kerem Shalom border crossing due to security concerns.[1318]
  • The NNA reported several blasts on the outskirts of Yaroun and Maroun al-Ras.[1323]
  • The Houthis said they had targeted a "vital target" in central Israel with a hypersonic missile.[1324]
  • Israeli security personnel carried out a raid in Seir village of Jenin area killing four men. The IDF said that that those killed were responsible for several gun attacks targeting Israeli towns in the border of northern West Bank.[1325]
  • An Israeli strike on a home in Beit Lahia killed at least 10 people.[1326]
  • The Nablus battalion of the Quds Brigades said that it clashed with Israeli soldiers in the eastern area of Nablus.[1327]
  • The IDF announced that soldiers from the Paratroopers Brigade killed several armed Hezbollah fighters near a church in southern Lebanon the previous night.[1328]
  • An Iranian airplane suspected of carrying arms to Hezbollah over Syrian airspace was ordered by Israeli fighter jets to turn around.[1329]
  • The Houthis claimed to have hit the US military supply ships Stena Impeccable, Maersk Saratoga and Liberty Grace and a destroyer using 16 ballistic and cruise missiles in the Arabian Sea and the Gulf of Aden.[1330] The United States Central Command said that it destroyed weapons launched by the Houthis.[1331]

2 December

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 37 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,466.[1332][a]
  • Far right Israeli National Security Minister Itamar Ben Gvir prohibited adhan in mosques in Israel.[1333]
  • France accused Israel of violating its ceasefire in Lebanon 52 times, causing the death of three Lebanese civilians.[1334] Israel rejected the accusations saying Israel is enforcing the ceasefire terms in the face of Hezbollah's violations of the ceasefire that require an immediate response in real time.[1335]
  • NNA reported that Israeli forces opened fire at homes in Naqoura with machine guns.[1336]
  • World Health Organization dropped off aid to Kamal Adwan Hospital. It also said that a team from Mercy International will be deployed in the hospital for a month to provide specialised medical staff.[1337]
  • The IDF again warned residents against returning to houses in some villages in south Lebanon.[1338]
  • The IDF announced that Israeli-American soldier Omer Maxim Neutra was killed during the 7 October attack and his body is held in Gaza based on new intelligence information.[1339]
  • A Israeli drone hit a Lebanese army bulldozer that was conducting “fortification work” at a Lebanese army base in the northeastern Hermel area, moderately injuring a Lebanese soldier.[1340]
  • The UN said that Gaza now has the highest number of child amputees per capita at the global level.[1341]
  • The IDF said that it struck Hezbollah military vehicles operating in a Hezbollah missile manufacturing facility in the Beqaa Valley. It also said that it struck Hezbollah vehicles used for transporting weapons at several sites in the border between Syria and Lebanon in Hermel District and conducted strikes against Hezbollah operatives in southern Lebanon.[1342]
  • The Gaza Government Media Office said that 3,700 people were killed or trapped under the rubble and 10,000 others were injured since the start of Siege of North Gaza.[1343]
  • Lebanese State Security said that one of its personnel was killed by an Israeli drone in Nabatieh.[1344]
  • Hezbollah launched two mortars towards Shebaa Farms, claiming that it was responding defensively to repeated ceasefire violations by the IDF.[1345] In response, the IDF struck dozens of Hezbollah members and rocket launchers, including the one used in the mortar attack.[1346] Six people were killed in Haris and four others in Talloussah.[1347][1348]
  • The al-Qassam Brigades said that it targeted IDF positions in Nirim and Ein HaShlosha using rockets.[1349]
  • Hamas claimed that 33 Israeli hostages were killed, mostly due to Israeli air strikes and some others due to botched rescue attempts by the IDF since the beginning of the war.[1350]
  • An Israeli strike on a school serving as a shelter in Jabalia killed a child.[1351]
  • An drone was launched from the east towards Israel.[1352]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for residents of five blocks in Khan Yunis.[1353]
  • An Israeli air strike in Marjayoun killed one person.[1354]

3 December

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 36 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,502.[1355][a]
  • Far right Israeli finance minister Bezalel Smotrich appointed a pro-settler activist as head of the agency overseeing Palestinian property in east Jerusalem.[1356]
  • The Food and Agriculture Organization said that food availability is at an all-time low throughout Gaza.[1357]
  • Hezbollah affiliated Al-Nour radio station announced that one of its journalists was killed in an Israeli strike.[1358]
  • The IDF renewed bans on people returning to their houses in over 60 villages in south Lebanon.[1359]
  • Two men were severely beaten by Israeli forces before arresting them in north of Bethlehem. It also arrested the deputy secretary of Fatah and two minors in the vicinity of Ramallah.[1360]
  • NNA reported that Israeli warplanes conducted a wave of strikes on a number of villages and towns in Tyre District and Bint Jbeil District. It also reported that the IDF launched flares and thermal balloons over Aita al-Shaab.[1361]
  • NNA reported an Israeli drone strike in Beit Lif.[1362]
  • The IDF claimed that one of its artillery units killed at least seven Hamas militants who participated in 7 October attack.[1363]
  • An Israeli strike on a car in Damascus airport road killed Salman Jumaa, Hezbollah's liaison with the Syrian army.[1364][1365]
  • The IDF said that it struck a militant cell in Aaqbeh village, Beqaa Governorate.[1366]
  • The Gaza Civil Defense Agency accused the IDF of targeting its crews while they tried to rescue and transport wounded Palestinians in Rafah.[1367]
  • The IDF claimed that it destroyed buildings used by Hamas and seized weapons during raids in the Netzarim Corridor.[1368]
  • The IDF issued evacuation orders for a majority of civilians in Beit Lahia.[1369]
  • An Israeli drone strike killed two civilians in Jabalia.[1370]
  • The al-Qassam Brigades said it clashed with Israeli forces using machine guns in Tubas.[1371]
  • The IDF arrested a doctor and a nurse from Tubas government hospital.[1372]
  • An Israeli strike on a residential building in Beit Lahia killed 12 people.[1373]
  • An Israeli drone strike in Shebaa killed one person.[1374]
  • The IDF said that it destroyed Hezbollah infrastructure in Shebaa Farms.[1375]
  • An Israeli strike on a house in Shati refugee camp injured several people including children.[1376]
  • UNRWA said that it distributed flour to approximately 9,000 families in areas throughout central Gaza through deliveries facilitates by World Food Programme.[1377]
  • The IDF claimed that two rockets were launched from northern Gaza towards Israel.[1378]
  • An Israeli raid in al-Mughayyir and eastern Nablus triggered confrontations with residents.[1379]
  • An IDF vehicle ran over a 17-year-old boy in Beita, Nablus.[1380]
  • An Israeli air strike on a UNRWA run school in Zeitoun neighbourhood of Gaza City killed six people and injured several others including at least one child.[1381][1382]
  • An Israeli strike in Sabra neighborhood of Gaza City wounded a boy.[1383]

4 December

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 30 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,532.[1384][a]
  • The Lebanese Health Ministry increased the death toll from Israeli attacks in Lebanon to 4,047.[1385]
  • The IDF claimed that its fighter jets bombed a vehicle carrying three Hamas militants who were planning to carry out an imminent attack in Aqqaba area of the Jordan Valley, killing them. The al-Qassam Brigades confirmed the death of two of its members.[1386]
  • Israeli forces shot dead a 15-year-old Palestinian teenager in the Silwan neighbourhood of East Jerusalem.[1387]
  • An Israeli strike on a home in the Abu Areef area, south of Deir el-Balah killed a Palestinian woman and wounded several others.[1388]
  • An Israeli drone strike hit Kamal Adwan Hospital, injuring three medical staff, one seriously.[1389]
  • Dozens of Lebanese families fled from south Lebanon again due to Israeli strikes.[1390]
  • An Israeli drone strike on a food distribution point and house in Nuseirat refugee camp killed five people including four children.[1391]
  • The New York Times reported that the IDF is constructing bases in central Gaza.[1392]
  • Israeli settlers attacked residents and set fire to property in Beit Furik and Huwara and attacked two Israeli border police officers after Israeli authorities evacuated an illegal settler outpost in the vicinity of Nablus.[1393]
  • Clashes erupted between Israeli soldiers and Palestinian fighters after Israeli forces stormed Qalqiya.[1394]
  • Israel's Coordinator of Government Activities in the Territories claimed that 122 trucks carrying humanitarian aid entered Gaza.[1395]
  • The IDF arrested at least 22 Palestinians including two children and a woman from the West Bank.[1396]
  • The IDF claimed that it destroyed militant infrastructure and killed several militants in air strikes and close-quarters fighting in Jabalia, adding that it found an explosives making laboratory in the area.[1397]
  • An elderly Palestinian man died after being severely beaten by Israeli forces in Aqraba, Nablus.[1398]
  • An Israeli air strike on two houses in Deir el-Balah killed at least two people and trapped several others under the rubble, most of them children.[1399]
  • The IDF detained five Israelis after they illegally crossed into southern Lebanon.[1400]
  • The al-Qassam Brigades claimed that it hit two Israeli Merkava tanks using rocket-propelled grenades and an explosive device in an intersection in central Beit Lahia and an Israeli troop carrier using an anti-armour shell in Jabalia. It also claimed that it killed two Israeli soldiers in the middle of Jabalia refugee camp.[1401]
  • The IDF said that six male hostages recovered dead in Khan Yunis over three months prior were most likely shot dead by Hamas guards based on pathological evidence. However, it also said that it cannot determine with complete certainty the precise cause of death of the hostages or the exact timing of the gunfire and it had no knowledge of the presence of hostages before its strike.[1402]
  • Two consecutive Israeli strikes in Israeli designated humanitarian safe zone of al-Mawasi killed at least 21 Palestinians including children and women, injured at least 28 others. One of those killed was a seven months pregnant woman.[1403] The IDF said that it killed several Hamas operatives including a top commander of internal security forces of Hamas, Osama Ghanim.[1404][1405][1406]
  • The IDF said that the IAF struck a Hezbollah launch pad in Majdal Zoun and destroyed combat equipment in Khiam, Sawwaneh and Aitaroun.[1407]
  • The IDF said that its joint operation with Shin Bet recovered the body of Israeli hostage Itay Svirsky from Gaza, claiming that he was earlier killed by Hamas guards in captivity.[1408]
  • Four multi-story buildings collapsed as a result of an Israeli strike in the Sheikh Radwan neighborhood of Gaza City, killing at least 25 people including children, injuring many others and trapping an entire family.[1409][1410][1411]

5 December

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 48 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,580.[1412][a]
  • Amnesty International accused the Netanyahu government and the IDF of genocide in Gaza. Israel's government denied the claim.[1413][1414]
  • The IDF said that it arrested a man who from a hospital in the West Bank who was a member of a militant cell which conducted a gun attack in Mehola Junction in August that killed an Israeli.[1415]
  • The IDF conducted three strikes in southern Lebanon.[1416]
  • The IDF arrested 28 people from the West Bank including a student from Qabalan, a 16-year-old boy from Hebron Governorate and the mother of two people killed by the IDF.[1417][1418][1419]
  • Israeli strikes hit water tanks of Indonesia Hospital, injuring three people.[1420]
  • The IDF said that it destroyed Hezbollah underground infrastructure and killed militants in southern Lebanon.[1421]
  • The IDF claimed that it killed seven Palestinian militants from the air and arrested 50 wanted individuals during its ground operation in West Bank in the past week.[1422]
  • Israeli strikes hit the Kamal Adwan Hospital, killing a 16-year-old boy who was in wheelchair after being discharged from the hospital and seven others and injured several others.[1423][1424][1425]
  • An Israeli strike on a residential building in Beit Lahia killed 15 people.[1426]
  • Israeli soldiers launched stun grenades towards a residential building in Aitaroun, inflicting injuries.[1427]
  • PIJ announced that three of its fighters were killed in Lebanon.[1428]
  • The IDF announced that 90,000 Palestinian civilians were evacuated from Jabalia, Beit Lahia, and Beit Hanoun. It said that it detained approximately 100 suspected militants and killed at least 1,750 militants since it launched its offensive against Hamas in the area in October, with approximately 20 killed during fighting in Beit Lahia in the previous day. Another 1,300 militants were detained.[1429]
  • An Israeli air strike in Aitaroun injured five people.[1430]
  • The al-Qassam Brigades said that it attacked an Israeli infantry force of 50 soldiers in Tal al-Hawa neighbourhood of Gaza City.[1431]
  • Gunfire broke out between Palestinian National Security Forces and armed groups in Jenin, which was blamed by the former on the theft of vehicles owned by the Palestinian Authority. However, the Jenin Brigades said that PA officers arrested one of its fighters and confiscated money that was for the family of a Palestinian fighter who was killed.[1432]
  • An Israeli air strike in Shujayea neighbourhood of Gaza City killed a three-year-old Palestinian child.[1433]
  • The IDF said that it killed Nidal al-Najar, the aerial unit chief of Hamas who helped oversee aerial infiltration into Israel during 7 October attack, in an operation done in collaboration with Shin Bet.[1434]

6 December

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 32 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,612.[1435][a]
  • Israeli forces injured a 16-year-old teenager during a raid in Jalazone refugee camp.[1436]
  • Heavy clashes were reported between Israeli forces and Palestinian fighters in Balata refugee camp. Israeli forces shot and killed a Palestinian man during those clashes.[1437][1438]
  • Israeli air strikes hit the Jousiya crossing and Arida crossing in the Syrian-Lebanese border. The IDF said that it struck routes used by Hezbollah for smuggling weapons.[1439][1440]
  • The Palestinian Red Crescent said that one of its emergency medics was shot and killed in Khan Yunis.[1441]
  • War monitors reported that Palestinian fighters continued to fight in Rafah, Gaza City, and Jabalia while a lull was reported in Beit Lahia.[1442]
  • A raid was reported on Kamal Adwan Hospital and it was reported that patients were forced to evacuate. Another strike reportedly hit the northern and western sides of the hospital, killing four staff members. The IDF denied responsibility.[1443][1444][1445]
  • Israeli shelling around the Kamal Adwan Hospital killed at least 33 people and dozens were injured.[1446][1447]
  • The IDF claimed that its air strike conducted in collaboration with Shin Bet killed Majdi Aqilan, deputy commander of the Shati Battalion of Hamas in northern and central Gaza who participated in the Nahal Oz attack, Ahmed Suwaidan, another Hamas commander, and Mamdouh Mehna, a senior member of the Hamas tunnelling unit.[1448]
  • Clashes erupted between residents and Israeli forces after soldiers raided Beit Furik, injuring three people.[1449]
  • United Kingdom Maritime Trade Operations reported that a merchant ship was listing and its crew were evacuated following an incident 105 nautical miles northwest of Hodeidah.[1450]
  • Wafa reported that Israeli forces detained three Palestinian journalists after assaulting them in the vicinity of Sinjil. It also reported that four other journalists who were briefly held were also subjected to abuse.[1451]
  • Wafa reported that an Israeli air strike hit a gathering of civilians in Kashkou Street in Gaza City's Zeitoun neighborhood, killing six people.[1452]
  • The IDF completely evacuated Kamal Adwan Hospital and ordered those evacuated to go through a checkpoint leaving the area. Seventy people were detained and taken to an unknown area for interrogation.[1453] The hospital was now only minimally functioning.[1447]
  • An Israeli air strike targeted a home in Nuseirat refugee camp that was evacuated before the strike, killing at least 26 Palestinians including six children and five women and injuring over 60 others, most of them women and children in nearby houses.[1454][1455][1456]
  • Israeli shelling hit tents housing displaced people in the vicinity of the western Nuseirat killing a young girl.[1454]
  • The IDF shot at Indonesia Hospital and ambulances in Beit Lahia. It also shot at Palestinians in Jabalia, Beit Lahia and Beit Hanoun. The Gaza Civil Defense Agency added that there are no more surgeons in Kamal Adwan Hospital.[1457]
  • Israeli warplanes flew over Beirut and hit a target in the vicinity of the Litani River between the Yohmor al-Chaqif and Zawtar al-Sharqiyah. The IDF blew up more buildings in Odaisseh. Israeli drones also flew at low altitude over the southern suburbs of Beirut.[1458]
  • The Al-Aqsa Martyrs' Brigades launched rockets towards Israeli forces along the Netzarim Corridor.[1459]
  • The IDF said that it found and destroyed a tunnel rigged with explosives in Rafah. It also said that it located stockpiles of weapons while operating in Rafah in recent days. It added that it killed members of a militia cell which mortared Israeli forces in the area.[1459]
  • A war monitor reported that the IDF was clearing Hezbollah weapons depots and military infrastructure in south Lebanon until 25 January.[1459]

7 December

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 52 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,664.[1460][a]
  • Israel's Coordinator of Government Activities in the Territories claimed that aid was delivered to Beit Hanoun.[1461]
  • A missile was launched from Yemen towards Israel.[1462]
  • A Palestinian was killed in an Israeli strike in the Israeli-designated safe zone of al-Mawasi.[1463]
  • Clashes broke out between Israeli forces and Palestinian fighters in Beita, Nablus during an IDF raid in the area.[1464]
  • Euro-Med Human Rights Monitor alleged that the IDF used detainees as human shields for evacuating hospitals in north Gaza.[1465]
  • An Israeli drone strike on a motorcycle in Deir Siryan killed one person.[1466]
  • Wafa reported an Israeli setter attack on Palestinians and their belongings east of Yatta, Hebron.[1467]
  • The IDF said that it struck a Hezbollah fighter who posed a threat to its soldiers in south Lebanon.[1468]
  • Two people were wounded in an Israeli settler attack in Taybeh, Ramallah. Another man was injured and his vehicle was damaged in an Israeli settler attack in Turmus Ayya.[1469]
  • Israeli settlers cut down 15 olive trees and vandalised a well in Salfit.[1470]
  • An Israeli strike hit a home housing displaced people in as-Saftawi, north of Gaza City killing four people. Another Israeli drone strike hit a group of people searching for flour east of Rafah.[1471]
  • Kamal Adwan Hospital ran out of electricity after Israeli gunfire hit its generators.[1472] An Israeli strike hit sections of the hospital including its intensive care unit, injuring four people including three children.[1473]
  • An Israeli air strike in Beit Lif killed five people and injured five others.[1474][1475]
  • A soldier of the 401st Brigade was killed by Hamas anti-tank fire in Rafah, increasing the IDF death toll in Gaza to 383.[1476]
  • Israel's Coordinator of Government Activities in the Territories said that more than 3,720 tons of flour were delivered in 218 trucks to Gaza.[1476]
  • A car ramming attack in Fawwar, Hebron critically injured an Israeli soldier. The IDF said that it was investigating whether bullets fired against the attacker hit a civilian car, slightly injuring a 45-year-old man. It also said that attacker who was wearing a shirt emblazoned with the Islamic State symbol was later shot and "neutralised" by a civilian security guard in Qalandia checkpoint.[1477]

8 December

See also: fall of the Assad regime and 2024 Israeli invasion of Syria
  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 44 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,708.[1478][a]
  • A missile was launched from Yemen towards Israel.[1479]
  • The IDF hit a convoy of Hezbollah vehicles containing fighters that departed from al-Qusayr, Syria.[1480]
  • Four IDF reservists, one of them holding a rank of major (res.), were killed near Labbouneh, south Lebanon. The soldiers were in an underground Hezbollah complex when an explosion occurred and an underground structure collapsed, killing them. The IDF said that, according to an initial probe, it is likely that the soldiers unintentionally triggered explosives rigged by the IDF.[1481][1482]
  • Houthis said that it targeted a vital facility in southern Israel using drones in an operation done with Islamic Resistance in Iraq.[1483]
  • Hours after the fall of the Assad regime, Israeli forces took complete control of the UN buffer zone in the Golan Heights, along with the towns of Khan Arnabah and Madinat al-Baath.[1484][1485][1486] Israel also took complete control of Mount Hermon after occupying the Syrian side of the mountain without resistance.[1487]
  • An Israeli air strike on camp for displaced people in Deir el-Balah killed five members of a family including children and wounded dozens of people.[1488]
  • An Israeli air strike on a residential home in Bureij refugee camp killed at least 11 people.[1488]
  • Israeli shelling hit Kamal Adwan Hospital, damaging electricity and oxygen pumps. Approximately 100 tank shells and bombs hit the hospital, injuring several medical staff and patients. The IDF claimed that Hamas operatives were using civilian buildings, including hospitals, which Hamas denied.[1488]
  • An Israeli airstrike hit Hezbollah members at a weapons depot in Dibbin.[1489]
  • The IDF said that it located and destroyed a large Hamas tunnel in Jabalia and killed Hamas operatives who emerged from the tunnel with an airstrike and fire from the ground.[1490]

9 December

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 50 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,758.[1491][a]
  • An Israeli strike on a tent in Az-Zawayda killed Raed Ghabaien, who was released from Israeli detention in 2014 and his wife.[1492]
  • A drone launched from Yemen damaged an apartment block in Yavne.[1493] Houthis claimed that it hit a sensitive Israeli target.[1494]
  • An Israeli strike hit people who lined up for buying flour in Rafah, killing 10 people.[1495]
  • An Israeli strike on a residential building in Bureij refugee camp killed at least nine members of a family, mostly women and children.[1495]
  • An Israeli air strike on a car on the Saf al-Hawa road in Bint Jbeil in the vicinity of a Lebanese army checkpoint killed one person and slightly injured four Lebanese soldiers.[1496]
  • Israeli police accused an Israeli man of burning cars and spray-painting messages for Iran.[1497]
  • An Israeli drone strike in Jabalia refugee camp killed three people who were attempting to searching for food.[1495]
  • Three Israeli soldiers of the Givati Brigade's Shaked Battalion were killed and 12 others were injured in a Hamas attack in Jabalia, increasing the IDF death toll in Gaza to 386.[1498]
  • An Israeli air strike on a building in northern Gaza sheltering a displaced family from Beit Lahia and Jabalia killed 22 people including children, women and elderly.[1499]

10 December

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 28 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,786.[1500][a]
  • The IDF said that it killed 10 Hamas operatives who were involved in the killing of three Israeli soldiers and injuring of 12 others in Jabalia one day prior in an air strike.[1501]
  • An Israeli airstrike on a multi-floored building in Beit Hanoun killed at least 10 people and wounded dozens.[1502]
  • The Israeli Navy detained six Palestinian fishermen who attempted to sail into the Mediterranean Sea.[1502]
  • An Israeli air strike on a home in Nuseirat refugee camp killed at least seven people including a woman and three children and injured several others. Palestinian footballer Mohamed Khalifa was also a victim of the strike. Three civilians were killed in a drone strike in northern Rafah city and two others were killed in another drone attack in the Shakoush area northwest of Rafah.[1499]
  • Israel's Coordinator of Government Activities in the Territories said that 201 trucks carrying humanitarian aid entered Gaza one day prior.[1503]
  • Houthis said that it targeted three supply vessels and two American destroyers in the Gulf of Aden.[1504] The US military said that it intercepted weapons launched by Houthis.[1505]
  • A car hit a pedestrian in Bnei Brak, slightly injuring him. Israeli police declared it as a terror ramming attack.[1506]
  • A 19-year-old man was killed and his 16-year-old relative was injured during clashes between Palestinian fighters and Palestinian National Security Forces in Jenin. The Palestinian National Security Forces admitted responsibility for his death.[1507]

11 December

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 19 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,805.[1508][a]
  • The Gaza Health Ministry said that 60 injured patients in Indonesia Hospital are at risk of dying because of lack of food and water.[1509]
  • An Israeli strike on a residential building in the vicinity of Kamal Adwan Hospital killed at least 22 people including women and children. The IDF said that it targeted a Hamas militant.[1510][1511][1512]
  • An Israeli strike hit the entrance of Kamal Adwan Hospital killing a woman and her two children.[1511]
  • Four projectiles were launched by militants from central Gaza towards Israel. The IDF issued evacuation orders for a five-block area of the Maghazi refugee camp, saying that rockets were fired from the area.[1511][1512]
  • The IDF said that it killed Salah Dahham, the head of paragliding unit of Hamas in Jabalia, who led aerial infiltration into southern Israel during 7 October attack. It also said that it killed Fehmi Salmi, a commander of Nukhba forces of Hamas in a separate airstrike, saying that he was responsible for an attack on an IDF outpost on the border with Gaza which killed 14 Israeli soldiers during 7 October attack and led numerous attacks on soldiers operating in Gaza during the war.[1513]
  • An Israeli strike hit a residential building in the Sheikh Radwan neighborhood of Gaza City killed five civilians including journalist Iman Al-Shanti and her son Bilal.[1510]
  • Israeli drone strike in the vicinity of Deir al-Balah Preparatory School killed one civilian and wounded several others.[1510]
  • An Israeli shelling hit a house in Az-Zawayda killing a child.[1510]
  • The IDF withdrew from Khiam in compliance with the ceasefire agreement.[1514]
  • Israeli strikes in three towns in southern Lebanon killed five people.[1515]

12 December

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 30 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,835.[1516][a]
  • A gun attack on a bus at a junction in Al-Khader killed an Israeli child and injured three other Israelis including a woman.[1517][1518]
  • Two Israeli strikes hit an aid convoy, killing 15 people and wounding at least 30, including several of them seriously.[1519][1520][1521] The IDF claimed that it struck two groups of Hamas militants who planned to loot trucks carrying humanitarian aid.[1522]
  • A drone was launched from Yemen and another drone was launched from the east.[1523][1524]
  • The IDF issued evacuation warnings for several neighborhoods of Gaza City after rockets were launched from the area towards Israeli soldiers operating in Gaza.[1525]
  • An Israeli strike on a residential building in al-Jalaa Street killed seven people including children.[1526]
  • The IDF said that an airstrike in Gaza City in this week killed Ammar Daloul, department head of weapons manufacturing division of Hamas who was also a company commander of Zeitoun Battalion of Hamas, Jihad Yassin who was a company commander of its Zeitoun Battalion, Yahya Masoud Muhammad Ashqar, who infiltrated into Israeli territory and participated in the 7 October attack, Hamas militants Kamal Saber Salim Arafat, Muhammad Muhammad Akram Aaraj, Loay Farid Faiz Hussein Ali who was a platoon commander of Hamas, Hamas militants Imad Aouni Ibrahim Rayan and Raed Samir Masoud Harazayn who was a member of internal security forces of Hamas.[1527]
  • The IDF said that it conducted a drone strike on Hezbollah members in southern Lebanon. The Lebanese Health Ministry and media said that one person was killed and another person was wounded in the strike in Khiam.[1528][1529][1530]
  • An Israeli drone strike killed Saeed Jouda, the only orthopedic surgeon in northern Gaza, while he was heading from Kamal Adwan Hospital to al-Awda Hospital.[1531][1532]
  • Israeli strikes hit a post office serving as shelter for displaced Palestinians and nearby homes in a residential area in Nuseirat refugee camp killing 36 people including women and children and injuring approximately 50 others. The IDF said that it targeted a senior PIJ leader whom it accused of attacking Israeli civilians and soldiers and accused PIJ of using civilian infrastructure and civilians as human shields.[1533][1534][1535]
  • The IDF said that it killed two militants in the West Bank.[1536]
  • Two people including a 15-year-old boy were wounded during an IDF raid in Beit Furik which triggered clashes between residents and Israeli forces.[1537]
  • Israeli forces forcibly evicted a Palestinian family from the third floor of their house in Jalbun and told them to leave for four days before converting it into a military outpost.[1538]
  • Israeli settlers set fire to a room and filled a water well with rubble in Jafaris area of the northern Jordan valley.[1539]
  • Three people were killed in an Israeli airstrike in Dibbine.[1540]

13 December

  • The Gaza Health Ministry reported that at least 40 Palestinians were killed in Israeli attacks in the past 24 hours, increasing the Palestinian death toll in Gaza to 44,875.[1541][a]
  • An Israeli strike hit the Nassr neighbourhood of Gaza City, killing three people including civilians.[1542]
  • At least three children including a 13-year-old boy were arrested by Israeli soldiers during a raid in Burqa, Ramallah.[1543]
  • NNA reported that the IDF conducted two air strikes in southern Lebanon.[1544]
  • Israeli strikes around Kamal Adwan Hospital wounded three medical staff, an ambulance was set ablaze and damaged the facility.[1545][1546]
  • The IDF said that it found and destroyed an underground rocket launch site in Beit Lahia. It also said that the IAF struck a militant cell that was approaching Israeli soldiers operating in Rafah and also located tunnel shafts, killed militants, and destroyed militant infrastructure sites in the same area.[1547]
  • Two projectiles were launched from central Gaza towards Israel. The al-Quds Brigades claimed responsibility for a rocket strike.[1548][1549]
  • The al-Quds Brigades said that it targeted IDF soldiers and vehicles in Rafah using mortar fire.[1550]
  • Israeli settlers uprooted almond, grape and banana trees owned by Palestinian farmers and destroyed the fense surrounding their land in Khirbet Tana et-Tahta. They also stole farmer's equipment.[1551]
  • The IDF said that its air strike struck militants who were on their way for conducting attack plans against Israeli forces in Gaza and Israel in the immediate future, claiming that they were in a Gaza City school. It added that it took many measures for decreasing the chance of harm to non-combatants. It also accused Palestinian militant groups of international law violation by operating in civilian infrastructure and using civilians as human shields.[1552]

14 December

  • The IDF destroyed buildings and dozens of houses in and around Beit Lahia.[1545]

  1550. ^ "Islamic Jihad says it attacked Israeli forces in Rafah". Al Jazeera. 13 December 2024. Al-Quds Brigades, the armed wing of Palestinian Islamic Jihad, says it targeted Israeli troops and military vehicles in Rafah in southern Gaza with mortar fire.
  1551. ^ "Israeli settlers uproot trees in the occupied West Bank". Al Jazeera. 13 December 2024. Israeli settlers have uprooted trees belonging to Palestinians in the village of Khirbet Tana, east of Nablus, in the occupied West Bank. Thaer Hanani, a coordinator of the campaign to defend Tana lands, told Wafa that settlers attacked him and several farmers, held him captive for over an hour and forced him to leave the area. When Hanani and the farmers returned to the site later on Friday night, they discovered that the settlers had uprooted several almond, grape and banana trees and that the fence surrounding the land had been destroyed. Hanani said the settlers had also stolen the farmers' equipment.
  1552. ^ "IDF: Airstrike targeted terror operatives who were heading to attack troops in Gaza". The Times of Israel. 13 December 2024.
